items.item_description: An assassin must have speed and cunning, yes, but also a backup blade for when things do not go to plan.

items.name: Horns of the Crypt Guardian
items.item_description: With these horns to protect his skull, none shall quench the soul-fire of Clinkz.

items.name: Gauntlets of the Crypt Guardian
items.item_description: Bone-hard gloves for bone-hard fists.

items.name: Demon Quiver of the Crypt Guardian
items.item_name: Demon Quiver of the Crypt Guardian
items.item_description: He's got eyes in the back of his back.

items.name: Royal Cape of the Great Grey
items.item_name: Royal Cape of the Great Grey
items.item_description: Red is the cape that drapes Lycan's neck, a symbol of the tainted blood that courses through his veins.

items.name: Sigil Belt of the Great Grey
items.item_name: Sigil Belt of the Great Grey
items.item_description: An protective iron belt hammered into the likeness of a wolf.  Long may the last of his house stalk the woods of Ambry.

items.name: Battle Claws of the Great Grey
items.item_name: Battle Claws of the Great Grey
items.item_description: These claws are the color of the moon, except when they are painted with the blood of enemies.

items.name: Housemark of the Great Grey
items.item_description: Lycan long ago gave up the crest of his acestral lands.  That crest died the day he was reborn a wolf, and now a new housemark is worn upon his shoulder.

items.name: Comb of the Great Grey
items.item_description: Wolf's mane, neatly combed.

items.name: Spellbinder's Forgotten Greatstaff
items.item_description: Rubick completely forgot about this greatstaff until just this moment!

items.name: Spellbinder's Tattered Cloak
items.item_description: It is difficult in battle for even a great mage to entirely avoid treading on his cloak. Eventually it begins to show wear.

items.name: Spellbinder's Catalytic Mantle
items.item_description: When Rubick dons his catalytic mantle, things really start happening.

items.name: Spellbinder's Mask of Shaping
items.item_description: Feeling ferocious, or simply for a lark, Rubick likes to take this old thing out and show it off from time to time.

items.name: Armor of the Twisted Arc
items.item_description: The Narrow Maze is lined with sharpened blades, but not the slightest scratch mars the surface of this hardened armor.

items.name: Belt of the Twisted Arc
items.item_description: Energy seethes through Razor's garb, ready to feed his whip with lethal power.

items.name: Bracers of the Twisted Arc
items.item_description: Protects Razor's forearms from inadvertent backlash.

items.name: Helm of the Twisted Arc
items.item_description: The twisted paths of the Narrow Maze are written on the inside of this mask, where Razor alone can study them.

items.name: The Twisted Arc
items.item_description: No weapon is more feared by the involuntary inhabitants of the Underscape.

items.name: Familiar of the Great Grey
items.item_description: As vicious as it is loyal, the familiar of the great grey is a powerful ally in any battle.

items.name: Form of the Great Grey
items.item_description: A form out of your worst nightmares.  The wolf is at your door.

items.name: Plates of Sundering
items.item_description: Unnatural growth of fungus, formed into structures hard as stone.

items.name: Roots of Sundering
items.item_description: A drink of the the tainted waters can change a being forever, Leshrac is capable of channeling great power through these branches.

items.name: Tail of Sundering
items.item_description: A transformation of a standard tail, into a weapon which pulses desolation.

items.name: Rack of Sundering
items.item_description: Simply touching these horns can corrupt the soul beyond repair.

items.name: Taunt: Sharp Blade
items.item_description: Watch as Juggernaut sharpens his blade by cutting down his foes!  Watch out!  That's a Sharp Blade!

items.name: Gloves of Retribution
items.item_description: Those who stand against the Skywrath can expect no mercy when Dragonus has them in his grip.

items.name: Taunt: The Magic Ends Here
items.item_description: Show their foul sorcery the regard it deserves.

items.name: Taunt: Shake Your Money Maker
items.item_description: Watch as Pudge "Shakes his Money Maker" while his foes cannot look away!

items.name: Taunt: Get Burned
items.item_description: Lina's Public Service Announcement ... "Hot Hot Hot!".  You have been warned!

items.name: Staff of Retribution
items.item_description: Skywrath Mage carries a special staff for every occasion. This one marks an occasion of retribution.

items.name: Helm of Retribution
items.item_description: The Skywrath Mage pierces his enemies with his gaze, shortly before he pierces them with his talons.

items.name: Belt of Retribution
items.item_description: The Skywrath, on errands of justice, gird themselves in cloth made of fibers found in the upper branches of trees so tall, there is no atmosphere there.

items.name: Pauldrons of Retribution
items.item_description: With shoulders high, Dragonus gazes far across the world to search those who have incurred the anger of the Skywrath.

items.name: Wings of Retribution
items.item_description: From high above the Ghastly Eyrie, a flutter of feathers drifts when Dragonus carries his earthbound foe to the heights...and lets them fall.

items.name: Bracers of Forsaken Beauty
items.item_description: Rubies stud these bracers. Medusa now mocks the beauty which she once held dear.

items.name: Bow of Forsaken Beauty
items.item_description: Twin snakes coil around a bow of wood and stone.

items.name: Blouse of Forsaken Beauty
items.item_description: A soft blouse from the days of her abandoned vanity.

items.name: Circlet of Forsaken Beauty
items.item_description: A circlet of golden laurels holds the delicate veil that hid Medusa's once-beautiful face.

items.name: Sweep of Forsaken Beauty
items.item_description: Silken cloths sweep the ground where Medusa wanders.

items.name: Frostiron Raider Helm
items.item_description: Denizens of the northern sea, the Frostiron Tribe are a proud people with a rich history.

items.name: Frostiron Raider Axe
items.item_description: The blacksmithing skill of the Frostiron Tribe has kept many a foe at bay.

items.name: Frostiron Raider Fist
items.item_description: Deceptively light yet incredibly durable, this glove was gifted to Tusk with the hope that it might ensure Ymir's safe return.

items.name: Frostiron Raider Shield
items.item_description: During his stay with the Frostiron Tribe, Ymir tried his hand at crafting armor.

items.name: Frostiron Raider Tusks
items.item_description: Masters of metals, the artisans of the Frostiron Tribe crafted steel tusks for Ymir as a symbol of his bravery.

items.name: Frostiron Raider Wrap
items.item_description: As Ymir wandered the great northern wilderness, he spent time among the Frostiron Tribe.  Upon his departure, he was given gifts to remember them by.

items.name: Helm of the Steppe
items.item_description: Near the height of his climb through the ranks of the arena, Bradwarden donned this helm, and could be recognized by cheering crowds when the first tip of horn appeared from the arena gates.

items.name: Frostiron Sorceress Brooch
items.item_description: The brooch is made of glacial sapphire carved by the artisans of the Frostiron tribe.

items.name: Frostiron Sorceress Cape
items.item_description: A tribe unknown to much of the world, the Frostiron are able to weave fabrics of incredible durability and warmth.

items.name: Frostiron Sorceress Cuffs
items.item_description: As fleeting spring came to the icy north, Ymir set off into the wilderness.  The warm seasons passed, and when winter returned so did he, bringing with him gifts and tales of a hidden tribe living near the coast.

items.name: Frostiron Sorceress Pads
items.item_description: The pads are deceptively durable, able to deflect even the strongest blow.  Such is the skill of the Frostiron Tribe that they remain as light as a snowflake.

items.name: Frostiron Sorceress Staff
items.item_description: The cool glow of an uncut glacial sapphire symbolizes the icy resolve of the Frostiron Tribe.

items.name: Summer's Bounty
items.item_description: Who would want to run away from such a beautiful spear?

items.name: Summer's Mirth
items.item_description: Mirth and merriment bedeck the lovely Enchantress. Ivy is cool in summer and who cares about winter anyway?

items.name: Summer's Light
items.item_description: Wearing these luminous pauldrons, Enchantress honors the glory of the summer sky.

items.name: Summer's Charm
items.item_description: Bedizened with oaken branches, Enchantress easily blends into the rich summer shade.

items.name: Summer's Warmth
items.item_description: Every warm summer day must eventually give way to the cool breezes of evening. This light covering is more than enough to ward off goosebumps.

items.name: Spaulder of the Steppe
items.item_description: Many a centaur was gored with this spiny spaulder.

items.name: Axe of the Red Conqueror
items.item_description: Red rules! Axe does not have time for other colors!

items.name: Helm of the Red Conqueror
items.item_description: When Axe wears this helm, Axe sees red. Which is perfectly fine with Axe.

items.name: Pauldron of the Red Conqueror
items.item_description: It seems a shame to cover Axe's mighty thews with pauldrons, but at least these are suitably red.

items.name: Tassets of the Red Conqueror
items.item_description: Axe girds his loins with tassets as red as his rage.

items.name: Gemmed Pauldrons of the Priest Kings
items.item_name: Gemmed Pauldrons of the Priest Kings
items.item_description: Worn heavy on the shoulders as a symbol that none may shrug off the responsibilities of faith.

items.name: Thrice-Gemmed Barding of Sanurok
items.item_description: Three times your steed has saved your life.  Three times you have graced its barding with a gem.

items.name: Gemmed Mitre of the Priest Kings
items.item_name: Gemmed Mitre of the Priest Kings
items.item_description: Worn only by the most revered, this headpiece symbolizes the highest attainment of the faith.

items.name: Gemmed Bracers of the Priest Kings
items.item_name: Gemmed Bracers of the Priest Kings
items.item_description: You are the strong right arm of the faith.  Also, the left arm.

items.name: Scarab Pendant of the Priest Kings
items.item_name: Scarab Pendant of the Priest Kings
items.item_description: This is no false idol, but an idol true, from which the sacred scarab of the faith may one day spread its golden wings and fly.

items.name: Ruling Staff of the Priest Kings
items.item_name: Ruling Staff of the Priest Kings
items.item_description: He is merciful.  Death is the mercy he offers, and this sacred staff the means by which it is granted.

items.name: Gunslinger's Hat
items.item_description: The perfect hat for a shootest accused of having bullets on the brain.

items.name: Gunslinger's Rifle
items.item_description: For the highland Keens, it is a matter of honor that each shootist construct his own weapon.  Thus a good shot is the product of both a sharp eye, and a keen mind for gun design.

items.name: Gunslinger's Bracers
items.item_description: Any article of clothing worn upon the body should be capable to carrying ammunition.  Even stylish bracers.

items.name: Gunslinger's Cape
items.item_description: By obscuring the profile, this cape has proven a useful countermeasure against long distance sniping.

items.name: Sleeves of the Charred Bloodline
items.item_description: The rubies sewn into the sleeves are prized among the Misrule nobility.

items.name: Heirloom of the Charred Bloodline
items.item_description: An heirloom of a once-noble house, now one with the ashes of history.

items.name: Style of the Charred Bloodline
items.item_description: Scorch them with style.

items.name: Gown of the Charred Bloodline
items.item_description: The dress was made in an old style once popular among the nobles of western Misrule.

items.name: Chopper of the Mad Harvester
items.item_description: Ain't nothing a bit of cutting can't improve.

items.name: Hook of the Mad Harvester
items.item_description: You want your meat tender, right?  Gotta bring it in close for that.

items.name: Rope of the Mad Harvester
items.item_description: If them intestines wanna be out, may as well put em to use!

items.name: Mask of the Mad Harvester
items.item_description: It's a lot funnier when the meat can't see what killed it.

items.name: Nails in the Mad Harvester
items.item_description: If there's a better way to keep a shoulder together, I ain't heard it.

items.name: Restraint of the Mad Harvester
items.item_description: If you're gonna strap a man down, make sure to use a sturdy table.

items.name: Regalia of the Bonelord Cape
items.item_description: The surviving subjects of a small kingdom known for its textile specialists fashioned this cape for Skeleton King in hopes that he would spare their lives. Which he did. (Just this once.)

items.name: Regalia of the Bonelord Sword
items.item_description: A sword fashioned for the Bonelord by some of his biggest fans in the smithing trade.

items.name: Regalia of the Bonelord Gauntlet
items.item_description: An item of extreme durability, imported from a land populated entirely by invertebrates who have never even heard of bone. (Do not mention this to Skeleton King!)

items.name: Regalia of the Bonelord Crown
items.item_description: Skeleton King takes crowns in tribute, and wears them both to strike terror into his enemies, and for a lark.

items.name: Regalia of the Bonelord Shoulder
items.item_description: Evil spikes serve as a reminder that slapping Skeleton King on the shoulder is both unseemly and dangerous.

items.name: Sweep of the Steppe
items.item_description: In the arenas of Omexe, it would not do to offer an opponent much of a grip.

items.name: Halberd of the Steppe
items.item_description: A ceremonial halberd, blooded often in the ceremonial battles of Omexe.

items.name: Girdpiece of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_name: Girdpiece of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_description: To enter Claszureme, one must study the workings of Clasz...and such endeavors require one gird oneself well.

items.name: Mantle of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_name: Mantle of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_description: Travelling between dimensions, followers of Clasz require protection from the chill interstitial spaces.

items.name: Gauntlets of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_name: Gauntlets of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_description: Hearing these gauntlets clanged together sharply in an aspect of prayer, the high essence of Claszureme responds with gifts of luck and protection.

items.name: Time-Mace of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_name: Time-Mace of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_description: One may be merely an acolyte, and yet have mastery of all the infinities of Clasz. For full knowledge of Claszureme, more dedication to dimensional defense is required.

items.name: Headwraps of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_name: Headwraps of the Acolyte of Clasz
items.item_description: No acolyte of Clasz needs eyes of flesh to observe the rites. Those who have them to begin with must soon part ways.

items.name: Crown of the Death Priestess
items.item_description: Death Prophet consecrates her union with death by donning this regal headdress. She only takes it off again with deep regret.

items.name: Dreadknight Gauntlet
items.item_description: Carved from obsidian, lined in gold, and adorned with the skull of the Deadknight himself; Ostarion loves nothing more than to display his former rivals.

items.name: Dreadknight Cloak
items.item_description: The sigils lining this cloak were said to render the Dreadknight invincible.  Ostarion proved otherwise.

items.name: Dreadknight Crown
items.item_description: From what little remained of the Dreadknight's shattered form was made this crown, a fearsome symbol of Ostarion's reign.

items.name: Dreadknight Pauldron
items.item_description: Aided by a fierce magnosceros, the Dreadknight set upon Ostarion's kingdom intent on conquest.  Now their bones do little more than decorate his unliving foe.

items.name: Dreadknight Blade
items.item_description: The sword and spine of the Dreadknight were fused and displayed in order to set an example for those that would dare challenge Ostarion.

items.name: Frost Owl's Beacon
items.item_description: Little hope remains to those lost in the frozen north, yet it is said that those able to summon an elusive Frost Owl will always find their way to safety.

items.name: Deep Vault Guardian Armplates
items.item_description: The sigil of the Deep Vault Guardians is engraved upon the cuff.

items.name: Deep Vault Guardian Spine
items.item_description: A guardian's spinal display serves as an identifier to his peers, and a warning to his foes.

items.name: Deep Vault Guardian Headfin
items.item_description: With fins flared, few would dare challenge a guardian of the Deep Vault for his charge.

items.name: Deep Vault Guardian Trident
items.item_description: Few creatures of the deep are able to heft such a heavy weapon, let alone weild it.

items.name: Nightwatcher's Belt
items.item_description: Those who patrol the Ghastly Eyrie on moonless nights take some comfort from their exclusive finery.

items.name: Nightwatcher's Bracers
items.item_description: In the dark of the Nightwatch, it is critical to be able to tell friend from foe at a glance. These distinctive bracers have prevented many a case of mistaken identity.

items.name: Nightwatcher's Mask
items.item_description: High rank among the Skywrath incurs the mingled honor and dread of equinoctial patrols among the Nightwatchers.

items.name: Nightwatcher's Guard
items.item_description: Dark things soar above even the Ghastly Eyrie. The raking of their talons must be guarded against.

items.name: Wicked Peacemaker
items.item_description: Centaur Warrunner would never run a war without preparing for peace!

items.name: Blade of Swift Victory
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Crest of the Wyrm Lords
items.item_description: The dragon comes for war.  He also comes with a big, heavy shield of dragon-forged steel on his arm.

items.name: NightHunters Wings
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: NightHunters helmet
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Form of the Onyx Grove
items.item_description: Among the northern pine did Sylla discover the darkness of the Onyx Grove, where creatures both fierce and strange gather to quarrel.  In time, the lone druid adapted his own form to join in the fray.

items.name: Armor from the Gloom
items.item_description: Within the haunted fields of the hereafter lie many useful arms for those with the ability to return to the living.

items.name: Belts from the Gloom
items.item_description: In the dim nether are shreds and shards of material, spectral matter lost in the ether.

items.name: Wights from the Gloom
items.item_description: The wild spirits beyond the veil are ever clawing and clinging to those that live.

items.name: Dress from the Gloom
items.item_description: Remnant fashion of a culture long lost to the ages.

items.name: Blindfold from the Gloom
items.item_description: Few can predict the price to be paid for piercing the veil.

items.name: Flying Desolation
items.item_description: Death flies when you're having fun.

items.name: Twin Serpent Bow
items.item_description: Beware the bite of the serpent bow.  There is no anitdote to an arrow in the chest.

items.name: Raven Scythe
items.item_description: What the white bird sows, the raven shall reap.

items.name: Spine Splitter
items.item_description: This sword doesn't even need to be sharp.

items.name: Headdress of the Protector
items.item_description: One can only speculate on the deep thoughts housed within golden confines of this reverent headdress.

items.name: Wavecutter
items.item_description: This fin will slice the water like its owner's blade will slice your throat.

items.name: Evildoer
items.item_description: The good we do dies with us, while our evils echo long after.

items.name: Aghanim's Basher
items.item_description: What could be better than an Aghanims scepter?  This.  This is better.

items.name: Formed Alloy Pauldrons
items.item_description:
Plates of steel with a trim is made of nickel-titanium. Ultimately, the dragon's teeth on the shoulders are just for looks.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Cauldron of Xahryx
items.item_description: Until at Sylla's paw the vile Xahryx fell asunder, the wildest power known was held within the cauldron's depths. In fear of what evil may seek such strength was the vessel taken, and put to heroic purpose.

items.name: Red Mist Reaper's Shawl
items.item_description: The sigil of the Red Mist Reaper binds the shawl.

items.name: Red Mist Reaper's Belt
items.item_description: In the Red Mist Army, cowardice was not tolerated.  Those who fled from battle were executed by the Reaper's scythe.

items.name: Red Mist Reaper's Mask
items.item_description: Though the mask hid the face of the Reaper, in truth all knew the identity of the executioner.

items.name: Red Mist Reaper's Tattoos
items.item_description: The position of Reaper carried responsiblity and conferred respect, expressed in these markings.

items.name: Red Mist Reaper's Scythe
items.item_description: The grim tool of an executioner in the Red Mist Army.

items.name: Flowering Treant
items.item_description: What appears to be a beautiful blossom is in fact the motile form of a cordyceps fungus which has infested the poor plant. It is still under the control of Nature's Prophet, but the ultimate outcome for the infected treant is far from pleasant.

items.name: Cranial Clap Trap
items.item_description: Skulls, it turns out, are a hindrance when one is attempting to chemically manipulate one's ogre.  Razzil has eliminated that obstruction.

items.name: Vengeancebound Wings
items.item_description: Upon hearing of his Beloved's fall at the hands of her sister, Dragonus pledged to bind his wings as a symbol for his failure to protect her.  The bindings are forged in arcane magic, causing excruciating pain whenever he takes flight.  A small price to pay, for he knows that though he can fly, she never will.

items.name: Craniomancer
items.item_description: A round head is an abomination.  So too, a round back.  Dark Seer now sports the cranium most ideal in all the universe.  In a battle of wits and wills, the pointiest head will often prevaile.

items.name: Aqwanderer Bracers
items.item_description: The Aqwanderer must travel the worlds, assess their strange peoples, and when necessary plot their destruction.

items.name: Aqwanderer Carapace
items.item_description: The swirling ions imbued within this shell offer all manner of practical protections.

items.name: Aqwanderer Crown
items.item_description: Special growths are conferred to the Aquanderer, so that they might better sense their surroundings and tune their thoughts toward strategy.

items.name: Aqwanderer Neckbrace
items.item_description: To become the Aqwanderer is to bear a heavy responsibility.

items.name: Aqwanderer Boots
items.item_description: Additional traction is often necessary on strange soils.

items.name: Wings of Impending Transgressions
items.item_description: His branded wings are bound and bandaged, though they remain forever unable to lift him into the light.

items.name: Bracers of Impending Transgressions
items.item_description: The better to kill and cauterize.

items.name: Tail of Impending Transgressions
items.item_description: This tail will swish till damnation come.

items.name: Pauldrons of Impending Transgressions
items.item_description: In the fires of the pit, these Pauldrons were forged of rancid steel and demon hide.

items.name: Sword of Impending Transgressions
items.item_description: A sword ever being forged, red hot, glowing with the heat of all the seven hells.

items.name: Tassets of Impending Transgressions
items.item_description: Around the belly of the beast is draped a belt demon armor, cast of finest steel, and hardened in the deepest pits of sixth hell.

items.name: Helm of Impending Transgressions
items.item_description: The helm hungers.

items.name: Thrashers of the Dreadful Abyss
items.item_description: In the darkened deeps are waters strange and pure.

items.name: Tendrils of the Dreadful Abyss
items.item_description: The terrors of the deepest depths of the oceans are hide aspects of subtle beauty.

items.name: Nomad's Shelter
items.item_description: The Highsand nomads learned long ago the value of a high collar.

items.name: Nomad's Guards
items.item_description: The links upon the surface offer protection yet remain lighter than a conventional guard.

items.name: Initiate's Cut
items.item_description: The simple hairstyle worn by an initiate of the Highsand nomad tribe.

items.name: Nomad's Barbed Edge
items.item_description: The weapons of the Highsand nomads may appear barbaric to some, yet each edge and curve is forged with careful purpose.

items.name: Nomad's Edge - Off-Hand
items.item_description: The weapons of the Highsand nomads may appear barbaric to some, yet each edge and curve is forged with careful purpose.

items.name: Wraps of the Blood Covenant
items.item_description: A deep bloodrage fuels the strength in your arms.

items.name: Mantle of the Blood Covenant
items.item_description: By the mantle of the Flayed Ones shall your enemies know you.

items.name: Belt of the Blood Covenant
items.item_description: The fabric of the sacred belt was stained with the blood of the Flayed ones.

items.name: Blade of the Blood Covenant - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Blade of the Blood Covenant - Off-Hand
items.item_description: Blood calls for blood.

items.name: Pads of the Blood Covenant
items.item_description: Armor against your blood-sworn enemies.

items.name: Blade of the Blood Covenant
items.item_description: An ancient weapon of finest steel, quenched in the blood of the Flayed ones.

items.name: Cowl of the Blood Covenant
items.item_description: He needs not eyes, who is guided by the sight of the Flayed ones.

items.name: Rachel the Morde-bat
items.item_description: Rachel ain't one for taking things easy.

items.name: Flamestitched Suitings Bandana
items.item_description: Do you know how hard it is to find a fireproof bandanna?

items.name: Flamestitched Suitings Wrap and Molotov
items.item_description: You mix it right, the world burns.  You mix it wrong, it burns a bit brighter!

items.name: Flamestitched Suitings Cape
items.item_description: Flyin' with style!

items.name: Battleseeker Arms
items.item_description: His Iron will shall break you.

items.name: Battleseeker Belt
items.item_description: The Beast of All Worlds is prepared for any battle.

items.name: Battleseeker Helmet
items.item_description: By his horns shall you know him, this unnatural beast from beyond the planes of reality.

items.name: Battleseeker Shoulders
items.item_description: Attack is the best defense.  Pauldrons also help.

items.name: Spines of the Dreadful Abyss
items.item_description: From strange waters come stranger properties.

items.name: Lost Hills Shield
items.item_description: Carved from the oldest trees of the thousand-league wood, this shield will protect old bones from attack.

items.name: Lost Hills Bow
items.item_description: With this bow, the fire of war is set.

items.name: Lost Hills Gauntlets
items.item_description: Fists of steel to go with your heart of fire.

items.name: Lost Hills Helm
items.item_description: Because most heat is lost from the head.

items.name: Lost Hills Shoulder
items.item_description: A little padding to keep your bones warm.

items.name: Heaven-Piercing Pauldrons
items.item_description: While purely decorative in nature, these ornate shoulder pieces serve as a reminder that even the depthless celestial realm is vulnerable to being punctured by Invoker's power.

items.name: Shade of Anguish
items.item_description: They will crave her. They will reach for her. They cannot have her.

items.name: Nature's Grip
items.item_description: A well-seasoned staff, suited to the hoary wisdom of a woodland prophet.

items.name: Guard of Anguish
items.item_description: A skull plucked from among the eager forsaken.

items.name: Dagger of Anguish
items.item_description: Dipped in the blood of many, willing and otherwise.

items.name: Meat Dragger
items.item_description: Sometimes the meat won't go nowhere unless you drag it.

items.name: Maze of Anguish
items.item_description: To be wrapped in her wings is to be trapped in her web.

items.name: Stone Infusion
items.item_description: "I can't feel my arm. Perfect."

items.name: Shadowshard - Off-Hand
items.item_description: A bit of the dark world, broken off and ready to pierce the flesh and drain away the soul.

items.name: Shadowshard
items.item_description: A bit of the dark world, broken off and ready to pierce the flesh and drain away the soul.

items.name: Chaos Knight's Armlet of Mordiggian
items.item_description: From sacrifice comes power.  From power flows chaos.

items.name: Mace of the Chosen
items.item_description: Weapons forged in the primal mists of the Font of Avernus may only be wielded by those the Font has chosen to defend it.

items.name: Abaddon's Raven Shoulders
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: The Dreaded Forgewing
items.item_description: They say fear lives in the skies, and soars above trailing flames in its wake.  They say an armor-clad terror drifts on the wind, snatching up the unsuspecting with a blazing lasso.  They say it's simple: if you see it, run.  And if it catches you, pray.

items.name: Entropic Helmet
items.item_description: Forged in a plane far upstream of the mortal world, the entropic helm can be worn only by the dark horseman.

items.name: Helm of Infernal Despair
items.item_description: Hope fails as lives shatter, and the dark form of chaos rides forth.

items.name: Possessed Blade
items.item_description: Few now have the skill to condense and compress a soul's raw energy into a blade.

items.name: Tribal Megadon Mask
items.item_description: While known as much for its incredible sharpness, the unpredictable structure of Radiant Ore means that very few such blades survive their first encounter.

items.name: Radiant Claive
items.item_description: While known as much for its incredible sharpness, the unpredictable structure of Radiant Ore means that very few such blades survive their first encounter.

items.name: Heat
items.item_description: Clinkz is not the only member of his clan to be preserved in a form of immortal bone. This bow, all that remains of his grandsire, is full of spirit fire and unwanted advice.

items.name: A Bit of Boat
items.item_description: A mutinous member of Kunkka's crew nearly made it to shore in this fateful craft. Tidehunter wields it as a reminder of that dread day, little knowing that Kunkka heartily approves of the message it sends to would-be deserters.

items.name: Crystalline Initio
items.item_description: Care to start something? You would be hard-pressed to find a better initiator than the Crystalline Initio!

items.name: Corruptor
items.item_description: Infused with pustulent power, Corruptor must feed on flesh or else Axe will suffer a troubling rash no apothecary's salves can soothe.

items.name: Spectral Light
items.item_description: When moving between certain dark angles of creation, it is important that one not be mistaken for prey. The sigils on this headpiece serve as a warning to some interdimensional predator, but an invitation to others less visible.

items.name: Wings of Vincere
items.item_description: The wings of pain take flight.

items.name: Crown of Vincere
items.item_description: The Queen wears her nightmare crown.

items.name: Guards of Vincere
items.item_description: There will be pain.  There will be screaming.

items.name: Mace of Vincere
items.item_description: The better to suffer fools.

items.name: Shoulder of the Atniw
items.item_description: Ferocity takes shape.  Huge shoulders rise to shrug off attack.

items.name: Robe of the Atniw
items.item_description: Fur is shed.  Nature's mysteries are revealed.

items.name: Cut of the Atniw
items.item_description: It has been too long since these bones felt combat.  White hair shall be streaked red from the blood of my enemies.

items.name: Hook of the Atniw
items.item_description: Nature chose her guardian well, as any true warrior chooses a weapon.

items.name: Braces of the Atniw
items.item_description: A projection of will.  A show of might.

items.name: Spirit of the Atniw
items.item_description: A projection of inner strength, and the bond of the bear clan.

items.name: Form of the Atniw
items.item_description: No foe shall stand against the true form!

items.name: Gauntlets of the Boreal Watch
items.item_description: A great archer once wore these magical gloves.  It is said that the strange runes there inscribed greatly improve the wearer's accuracy in battle.

items.name: Legplates of the Boreal Watch
items.item_description: Lightweight and durable, these resilient legplates have stood the test of time, and grueling battle.

items.name: Longbow of the Boreal Watch
items.item_description: Only those attuned to frost may pull back the bowstring of the Tundra Walker.

items.name: Cowl of the Boreal Watch
items.item_description: For those who wish their face never to be seen.

items.name: Pauldrons of the Boreal Watch
items.item_description: Forged by the Northern Drow from the ore of the chasm, these pauldrons bear the mark of the Boreal Watch.

items.name: Quiver of the Boreal Watch
items.item_description: Fluted with the plumes of the great arctic arcoch, and bathed in the runoff of the blueheart glacier, these arrows are said to freeze targets to the core.

items.name: Cloak of the Boreal Watch
items.item_description: Three layers of cloth and fur help to guard against the northern winds.

items.name: Spines of the Predator
items.item_description: Spiked carapace!

items.name: Mind Piercer of the Predator
items.item_description: Nyx's words enter the mind with great subtlety.  His horn enters the mind with considerably less subtlety.

items.name: Preyfinders of the Predator
items.item_description: Nyx's purpose draws nigh.  Your death is his purpose.

items.name: Blades of the Predator
items.item_description: By these blades, Nyx's enemies go the way of all flesh.

items.name: Helm of the Hypnos
items.item_description: You can't run from your thoughts.  But Nyx wants you to try.

items.name: Dragon Forged Armor
items.item_description: Forged in the plasmic residue of a star called Dragon, this armor protects as no mere dragon hide ever could.

items.name: Dragon Forged Stare
items.item_description: Their sanity I'll shatter.  Their dreams of conquest I'll destroy.

items.name: Dragon Forged Staff
items.item_description: Small minds are quickly broken.  With this mace, small bodies, even quicker.

items.name: Dragon Forged Wings
items.item_description: The Harbinger bears dark tidings on swift wings.

items.name: Arctic Bracers of the North
items.item_description: Brace yourself for cold and snow in these beautiful arctic bracers.

items.name: Frostbitten Cloak of the North
items.item_description: Ice is nice!  Except in cases of frostbite, so stay warm in this downy cape.

items.name: Ice Capped Hood of the North
items.item_name: Ice Capped Hood of the North
items.item_description: Behold the scourge of Icewrack! Now in this stylish hood.

items.name: Wizardry Staff of the North
items.item_description: With this staff, your enemies fate will be crystal clear.

items.name: Shoulders of the North
items.item_description: Keep the snow off your shoulders in these furry shoulders of winter.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's Second Chance
items.item_description: For when both a sword and a pistol still won't do.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's First Chance
items.item_description: For when a sword won't do.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's Gloves
items.item_description: The quality of an admiral's gloves is directly related to how well they can grip a sword.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's Helm
items.item_description: The steel sweep and sprouting brush are said to be of Kunkka's own design.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's Treads
items.item_description: When you walk the deck, make sure they know who's in charge.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's Chestplate
items.item_description: Don't let the plate fool you; he'd much rather the jacket survived the battle unharmed.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's Elegant Pauldron
items.item_description: If you're going to travel, do it in style.

items.name: Claddish Voyager's True North
items.item_description: On his voyage, True North will show him the way.

items.name: Blade of Shattered Crystals Off-Hand
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: The Ol' Chopper's Grizzled Face
items.item_description: Some folk talk about a crazy man up in them woods, finding and cutting on those what come through. But I know better. I ain't crazy.

items.name: Sacred Orb Carapace
items.item_description: Once in a thousand cyclings of the hive, Nyx grants one of her Assassins the Carapace of the Sacred Orb. It is the most painful of molts...but legend requires great sacrifice.

items.name: Whispering Dead Armor
items.item_description: The wandering dead speak through the boneguard.

items.name: Whispering Dead Mask
items.item_description: Carved of imbued bone so that Lanaya might speak with those beyond death, this mask was a gift from the Unseen Seven.

items.name: Whispering Dead Mantle
items.item_description: Merely a skull to the living observer, yet to the dead it shines as a beacon.

items.name: Ataxia
items.item_description: On burning hooves it strides, a beast ever eager for the fires of chaos.

items.name: Blade of Endless Havoc
items.item_description: Ever its edge thirsts for battle, for war, for chaos.

items.name: Helmet of Endless Havoc
items.item_description: Forged in the tumult of the rift, the helm burns eternal.

items.name: Shield of Endless Havoc
items.item_description: Let them loose their arrows and fling their axes.  The shield cares not.

items.name: Mantle of Endless Havoc
items.item_description: Heavy is the burden of unending war, yet many are its vicious pleasures.

items.name: Sacred Orb Helm
items.item_description: The Nyx Assassin, under the influence of the Sacred Orb, perceives even more of Nyx's bounty: So many targets to reap!

items.name: Sacred Orb Venom Claws
items.item_description: Against certain foes, the Nyx assassin imbues its blades with a venom that is their only weakness. Praise Nyx that they have even one such vulnerability!

items.name: Tidehunter Blink Dagger
items.item_description: Accurate or not, an untrustworthy anemone convinced Tidehunter that his blink dagger would have extra blinking power with this optional organic power-pack.

items.name: Wolfhound Rifle
items.item_description: This intricately crafted lever-action rifle is inspired by the deadly precision of canine predators.

items.name: Flaming Scepter of Ancestral Luck
items.item_description: By rights it came to Aggron, and by luck it happened to be on fire!

items.name: Bracer and Band of Ancestral Luck
items.item_name: Bracer and Band of Ancestral Luck
items.item_description: Rare is the ogre that can recall their lineage and lucky is the one with claim to an inheritance.

items.name: Mantle of Ancestral Luck
items.item_description: The ogres of the elder days were said to be great builders and skilled artisans... by ogre standards.

items.name: Belt of Ancestral Luck
items.item_description: A sturdy belt, comfortable, even fashionable among ogre-kind, yet in truth Aggron was disappointed that the elder's lockbox in which it was found did not contain a few scraps of moldy food.

items.name: Masks of Ancestral Luck
items.item_description: The names of the twin leaders who once owned these masks have been lost to ignorance.

items.name: Jewel of the Forest Gloves
items.item_description: We all know what Drow herself will never admit: She is the true Jewel of the Forest. And thus these gloves are perfectly fitting.

items.name: Jewel of the Forest Pauldrons
items.item_description: Jewels for a jewel.

items.name: Jewel of the Forest Boots
items.item_description: Their fleet-running beauty gleams and shimmers, deep in the forest shade.

items.name: Black Boots of the Voyager
items.item_description: Note the blade stowed away in the left boot, suitable for carving wood, cutting ropes, and whittling Tidehunter's name in the deck.

items.name: Green Sleeves of the Voyager
items.item_description: For who else but my captain, Green Sleeves?

items.name: Ernest Do of the Voyager
items.item_description: There are three kinds of people that go around beardless: boys, women and amphibians! And I am emphatically none of these things!

items.name: Button Down of the Voyager
items.item_description: A dozen brass buttons, and triple-stitched by a master sailmaker, it would take an unusually determined prospective mate to surmount this formidable fortress of...chastity?

items.name: Firebreather of the Voyager
items.item_description: Carried mainly for show, Kunkka does find Firebreather's flintlock a reliable means of lighting his pipe in inclement weather.

items.name: Blue Stone Shoulder of the Voyager
items.item_name: Blue Stone Shoulder of the Voyager
items.item_description: Kunkka is no pirate. Still, the stones were just lying there and would have gone to waste had he not seized them. Technically, that might well constitute plundering.

items.name: Compass Edge of the Voyager
items.item_description: A blade that invisibly orients its victim's soul to true death.

items.name: Jewel of the Forest Bow
items.item_description: Jewels of the Forest are in fact a fossilized sap, a richly colored amber from woods that were ancient when the drow folk took up residence there.

items.name: Jewel of the Forest Cape
items.item_description: A jewel deserves the perfect surrounds to show its stunning beauty to best advantage.

items.name: Jewel of the Forest Scarf
items.item_description: A brilliant jewel must shade itself at times, lest it be spied by greedy eyes.

items.name: Nightwatcher's Staff
items.item_description: The Nightwatcher's Staff offers a subtle line of defense against whatever might swoop down from the open reaches of space, to prey on the Ghastly Eyrie.

items.name: Deep Warden's Prized Scimitar
items.item_description: No weapon was more prized among the warden's private collection, nor more missed when it vanished.

items.name: Deep Warden's Conch Pauldron
items.item_description: They say a glow conch can fetch a pretty penny on the black market.

items.name: Deep Warden's Tooth Bracer
items.item_description: If you're going to go through all the trouble of breaking out of prison, you may as well take a few souvenirs!

items.name: Deep Warden's Darkray Cape
items.item_description: There's not a lot to a darkray, but you'll find what's there to be pretty durable.

items.name: Deep Warden's Seized Hood
items.item_description: They say the thief that used to own this hood killed eleven guards before he was finally sent up for air.

items.name: Bladebreaker Armguards
items.item_description: Each member of the Bladebreaker Order is equipped with barbs along their wrist, meant to catch and shatter an enemy sword.

items.name: Bladebreaker Hood
items.item_description: The hood is colored to represent the Bladebreaker order.

items.name: Bladebreaker Dagger - Off-Hand
items.item_description: According to the Bladebreaker Order, only those that must will die. The notches atop the hilt are meant to capture and turn enemy swords in the hopes that the disarmed opponent might flee instead of fight.

items.name: Bladebreaker Spaulders
items.item_description: The Bladebreaker Order favors disarming and sparing their opponents over direct combat.

items.name: Sleeves of the Scorching Princess
items.item_description: The sleeves flare out like the fiery soul who wears them.

items.name: Dress of the Scorching Princess
items.item_description: In commissioning this dress, the lord of Misrule discovered all too quickly how expensive fireproof cloth can be.

items.name: Tails of the Scorching Princess
items.item_description: A style fit for a princess.

items.name: Epaulettes of the Scorching Princess
items.item_description: In trying to woo Lina for his son, the lord of Misrule commissioned finery to make Lina more presentable to the royal court.

items.name: Tahlin Occult Dagger
items.item_description: There are none so stabbed as those who will not see.

items.name: Tahlin Occult Dagger - Off-Hand
items.item_description: A blade lifted from the corpse of Riki's father on the night that House Tahlin fell, this blade has been sheathed in many foes.

items.name: Tahlin Occult Shoulder Sigil
items.item_description: Enscribed with the symbol of the house of Tahlin, this shoulder mark is a symbol to all with the eyes to see it.

items.name: Bladebreaker Brush
items.item_description: Balance can be a prickly thing. So is this counterweight.

items.name: Cloak of the Northern Wind
items.item_description: In certain parts of certain worlds, the Northern wind blows warm, with a promise of eternal spring.

items.name: Arc of the Northern Wind
items.item_description: The gift of a grateful spirit, this bow honors Lyralei's intervention in the rescue of a doomed forest to which she owed nothing.

items.name: Pauldrons of the Northern Wind
items.item_description: Generations from now, the denizens of Njord's Hearth shall know Windranger by these pauldrons should she ever return to their demesne.

items.name: Quiver of the Northern Wind
items.item_description: Held safely in this quiver, Windranger's arrows defy the threat of cold winds that might cause their sinews to crack.

items.name: Circlet of the Northern Wind
items.item_description: Worn proudly wherever she goes, Lyralei reminds the world that it is her business to turn back the inevitable, and discover victory where others have foretold defeat.

items.name: Starlight Armguards
items.item_description: The light of the uncountable stars shines out with a protective power.

items.name: Starlight Dress
items.item_description: Mirana's garb illumines the Nightsilver woods as she rides among the darkling trees.

items.name: Starlight Band
items.item_description: This Starlight Band is the perfect accoutrement for calling down Starfall.

items.name: Starlight Quiver
items.item_description: Arrows that shine with captive starlight are barely contained in this glowing quiver.

items.name: Morcant
items.item_description: This pale creature found its way down the starlight path as if it heard its future mistress calling.

items.name: Starlight Finery
items.item_description: Mirana decks herself in the subtle hues of a moonless night.

items.name: Starlight Bow
items.item_description: The light that fills this bow left its home a trillion trillion lightyears past. But it finds her enemies NOW.

items.name: Bladebreaker Dagger
items.item_description: According to the Bladebreaker Order, only those that must will die. The notches atop the hilt are meant to capture and turn enemy swords in the hopes that the disarmed opponent might flee instead of fight.

items.name: Redmoon Assassin's Secret Armor
items.item_description: When the master of the Redmoon Order offered to indoctrinate Lanaya in its particular mysteries, she hesitated to know more...until she caught a glimpse of this mysterious armor.

items.name: Redmoon Assassin's Secret Headwear
items.item_description: So keenly tuned are the senses of the Redmoon Order's ancient foes that even a stray hair can betray an assassin's presence.

items.name: Redmoon Assassin's Secret Wraps
items.item_description: Lanaya moves in a hushed and secret silence that has never been more mysteriously complete.

items.name: The Ol' Chopper's Cleaver
items.item_description: It's dull, but it's heavy.  When it's to bone and meat, heavy counts for more.

items.name: The Ol' Chopper's Choppin' Arm
items.item_description: This the arm I do me choppin' with!

items.name: Chained Wings
items.item_description: Let her have you, and she will keep you.

items.name: The Ol' Chopper's Chains
items.item_description: I once made me a bracelet with a bit of spare ankle, but it kept coming apart. Some chain helped with that.

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Mantle
items.item_description: Such a style has never been seen near Xhacatocatl, but the Hound of the Flayed Twins must on occasion roam far from his accustomed lands.

items.name: The Ol' Chopper's Meat Jacket
items.item_description: Why go to the trouble of a proper butcherin' if you can't show it off?

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Hood
items.item_description: In the land where executions are accomplished by gallows, Strygwr shadows his face that the thirst of the Twins that burns in his eyes may go unremarked by suspicious passersby.

items.name: The One Horn
items.item_description: What age is this, when any mundane mount can be converted to a mythical beast with the simple installation of a uni-horn and silken mane? An epic age indeed!

items.name: Dreaded Bravo's Scarf
items.item_description: When pursuing arcane leads in the desert ruins of Halgalareh, even an assassin can justify adopting a bit of the local color.

items.name: Dreaded Bravo's Cape
items.item_description: The sands of Halgalareh are all that remain of a vast empire of prismatic towers. To inhale them is to breathe fine shards of glass. So it is not secrecy alone that dictates the wearing of this colorful veil.

items.name: Dreaded Bravo's Guise
items.item_description: At night, the moon above Halgalreh's ruins casts an hallucinatory light that curdles the mind as surely as the blazing sun broils an uncovered skull throughout the day.

items.name: The Ol' Chopper's Dinner Bringer
items.item_description: Y'know, someone once told me it ain't the hook catching you that really hurts, but when I take it back out.

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Back
items.item_description: Although he wears the garb of a benighted foreign land, Bloodseeker still relies on sacred lines of power to channel the blood he lets.

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Gauntlets
items.item_description: Hempen ropes are a crude tool for execution, but Bloodseeker seeks to understand the ways of the backwards lands through which his hunting takes him.

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Skirt
items.item_description: Bloodseeker found many uses for the gallows rope he stole from a corpse's distended neck, in order to study this crude means of execution at his leisure.

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Blade
items.item_description: It is sometimes necessary, in his travels, to forego his accustomed blades of volcanic glass and fall back on something fashioned by the local smith.

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Blade - Off-Hand
items.item_description: It is sometimes necessary, in his travels, to forego his accustomed blades of volcanic glass and fall back on something fashioned by the local smith.

items.name: Belt of the Eternal Light
items.item_description: Spectre's notion of light is not like that of other beings. Nor is her understanding of eternity.

items.name: Teeth of the Eternal Light
items.item_description: Forged in a realm best left forgotten, these teeth induce agony from nerves that reach beyond mortal experience.

items.name: Chestpiece of the Eternal Light
items.item_description: A nightmarish reminder of the mystery that lies shielded in bewilderment at Spectre's heart.

items.name: Encasement of the Eternal Light
items.item_description: A gem of wisdom? A polished lense of eldritch insight? A dimension-straddling insect's eye? Spectre answers not.

items.name: Plume of the Eternal Light
items.item_description: Neither feather nor foliage, nor quite a blend of both, the being from which these plumes were plucked dwells in the eternal light of a realm unseen, which Spectre navigates by senses that have no mundane equivalent.

items.name: Wise Cap of the First Light
items.item_name: Wise Cap of the First Light
items.item_description: The First Light, as it shines out upon creation, is bright beyond comprehension. One cap shades the eyes from its brilliance; the other allows Ezalor to gaze into it straight on.

items.name: Gladys the Light-Bearing Mule
items.item_description: Ezalor keeps the Light; Gladys keeps Ezalor.

items.name: Spiral Staff of the First Light
items.item_name: Spiral Staff of the First Light
items.item_description: A twisted staff that holds a captive memory of the initial blaze of creation.

items.name: Bardings of the First Light
items.item_description: Woven with the finest silk and plaited with the most exquisite gold, these garments are worth not even a single hair from Gladys' great mane.

items.name: Robes of the First Light
items.item_description: Much like Gladys, these robes have followed Ezalor since the dawn of the first day.

items.name: Kunkka's Shadow Blade
items.item_description: Often the tides of war go unseen until it is too late.

items.name: Breastplate of the Slithereen Knight
items.item_description: As strong as it is beautifully crafted, this breastplace armor provides protection against the hazards of the deep.

items.name: Helm of the Slithereen Knight
items.item_description: This helm and golden headpiece has long been a symbol of command among the Knights of the Slithereen.

items.name: Bite of the Slithereen Knight - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Bite of the Slithereen Knight - Off-Hand
items.item_description: By blade and song, the wet-work specialist earns her place in the Slithereen Guard.

items.name: Tail of the Slithereen Knight
items.item_description: The better to slither hither.

items.name: Might of the Slithereen Knight
items.item_description: With this sword, truly, no Slithereen may fail.

items.name: Tahlin Occult Hood
items.item_description: A trickster's hood to hide your eyes.  But it will take a trickster's heart to hide your sins.

items.name: Entropic Axe
items.item_description: Since the moment of the great schism, the dark rider has hunted.  He now rides with blackened iron in his fist--a battle axe of entropy forged in the chaos between the stars.

items.name: Old Ironsides Pauldrons
items.item_description: Step lively now, your Admiral has come aboard sporting these lightweight storming pauldrons.

items.name: Old Ironsides Gauntlet
items.item_description: With rough seas ahead, these lightweight gauntlets of blued steel will help you survive the stormiest of battles.

items.name: Old Ironsides Prow
items.item_description: A Claddish officer's prow with a carved figurehead of Lady Locke, the merry Duchess of the Isles.

items.name: Leviathan Whale Blade
items.item_description: Upon the rough seas swam the wondrous and terrible leviathan whale, set upon consuming ship and crew, and when it had eaten its fill did it vanish into the roiling waves leaving stranded those in its wake. Forged by one that lived, the blade ever seeks the heart of the beast.

items.name: BladeBiter
items.item_description: Sharp as shark's teeth, and strong as Claddish steel, the great sword Bladebiter is an asset to any sailor facing battle.

items.name: Entropic Shield
items.item_description: By shield and blade, the dark horseman bequeaths chaos.

items.name: Entropic Shoulderpads
items.item_description: Knight in Blackest armor.  Where the horsemen ride, death shall follow.

items.name: Aether-Wings
items.item_description: Puck's wings exist in a realm slightly offset from the rest of it, and are subject to unsynchronized molts and unpredictable fluctuations of form.

items.name: Dragon Sword
items.item_description: A blade inspired by a dragon's fire. Warning: May contain actual soul of dragon.

items.name: Broken Shackles
items.item_description: It is unwise, and often quite fatal, to underestimate an ogre's strength!

items.name: Prisoner's Anchor
items.item_description: They say you won't go far with one of these. They're wrong.

items.name: Storm-Stealer's Armor
items.item_description: All the sweeter for being stolen, Razor wears an armor alive with the energy of the storms he has angered.

items.name: Gift of the Sea Arms
items.item_description: Among the greatest of gifts offered to Morphling, these fines that separate tangible body from ineffable soul.

items.name: Scree'auk's Talon
items.item_description: Scree'auk's Talon was fashioned by a certain winged Mage, forged from shades of unrequited passion, tempered in grief, and quenched in the secret tears of her admirer. More's the pity that she uses it now, approximately half the time, to hunt him.

items.name: Nyx Assassin's Dagon
items.item_description: The blessings of Nyx upon her anointed assassins oft bring with it strange energies.

items.name: Whalehook
items.item_description: Ideally, a hook made for reeling in enormous creatures of the deep would not gouge and hack into the bones and flesh of the prey. But Pudge doesn't much care if he makes a mess of his meat.

items.name: Admiral's Prow
items.item_description: Taken as tribute from the head of a defeated captain after the first battle of Trembling isles, the Admiral's Prow is one of Kunkka's proudest war trophies, and a hat worthy of a master sailor.

items.name: Storm-Stealer's Bracers
items.item_description: Razor crackles with power--stolen power.

items.name: Cloak of the Dark Wraith
items.item_description: Mortred's choice of garb is as mysterious as her choice of target.

items.name: Girdle of the Dark Wraith
items.item_description: In hushed voices, they whisper of lessons learned in a distant land known as Lordran. What can it mean?

items.name: Helm of the Dark Wraith
items.item_description: A helm as dark as her soul.

items.name: Guard of the Dark Wraith
items.item_description: Wraithlike, she passes unseen. But should you espy her, you would appreciate the graceful lines of her garb.

items.name: Blade of the Dark Wraith
items.item_description: A reminder that the Dark Wraith's full attention is equivalent to death.

items.name: Chained Beauty
items.item_description: Be vicious, be beautiful.

items.name: Gift of the Sea Fin
items.item_description: A fragment of a sea-serpent's tail? A crystalline imprisonment of the sea's energy? Not even the enigmatic Morphling would hazard a guess.

items.name: Storm-Stealer's Belt
items.item_description: Paraded with pride, Razor flaunts the power he draws from electric skies.

items.name: Gift of the Sea Head
items.item_description: Crowned with ambition and innate knowledge of the depths, Morphling wears these shimmering scales with eldritch pride.

items.name: Chained Spur
items.item_description: Delight in pain as they squeal with agony.

items.name: Gift of the Sea Shoulders
items.item_description: Who can say no to such a glorious gift of strength and power?

items.name: Chained Guard
items.item_description: A little armor can go a long way.

items.name: Storm-Stealer's Helm
items.item_description: Razor hides his face beneath this helm, that no lightning-lashing storm may recognize him.

items.name: Gift of the Sea Dorsal Wings
items.item_name: Gift of the Sea Dorsal Wings
items.item_description: The sea's first gift was swiftness, imbued in these winglike dorsal fins.

items.name: Prestidigitator's Wraps
items.item_description: To fool? To trick? To deceive? Never question a sorcerer's whim!

items.name: Prestidigitator's Oculus
items.item_description: A true trickster can see through the wiliest of ways.

items.name: Prestidigitator's Shiners
items.item_description: Untruth and beguilement are ever a conjurer's allies.

items.name: Prestidigitator's Source of Sorcery
items.item_description: Beware he who reaches beyond to the root of duplicity!

items.name: Robes of Malicious Efflorescence
items.item_description: A billowing flow of haunted light plays about a dreaded form.

items.name: Blades of Malicious Efflorescence
items.item_description: Unfolding, unfurling, unyielding, unstoppable.

items.name: Horns of Malicious Efflorescence
items.item_description: Into the mortal universe pierce the horns of purest strife.

items.name: Bracers of Malicious Efflorescence
items.item_description: Of flowing dark and unknown aethers come arms of dangerous beauty.

items.name: Wings of Malicious Efflorescence
items.item_description: Charged energies hold tight to a shadowy being.

items.name: Tabard of the Crested Cannoneer
items.item_description:
The bravery of the Claddish cannon crew shall always be honored.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Cannonade
items.item_description:
Within an admiral's hand Cannonade shines brightly, pointing the way for the blast to come.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Tails of Resonant Vibrance
items.item_description: The nether whips and the ether swirls, and yet such beauty eludes those who lack the discipline to pierce the mundane.

items.name: Hood of Resonant Vibrance
items.item_description: There is little that cannot be understood by one trained to know the powers beyond.

items.name: Shawl of Resonant Vibrance
items.item_description: To harness such unpredictable power is a heavy burden. Or so say those who have not yet learned to turn back gravity!

items.name: Focus of Resonant Vibrance
items.item_description: To focus and bend the wild, unseen energies to one's whim is a skill few possess!

items.name: Armour of the Exiled Ronin
items.item_description: Made to endure the harshest of elements, including... blade storms.

items.name: Storm-Stealer's Whip
items.item_description: With a power seized from nature at its nastiest, Razor lashes the Narrow Maze's victims toward their end.

items.name: Viridus Crusher
items.item_description: A weapon that makes sense only in the Chapels of Claszureme. And even then, only barely.

items.name: Viridus Claw
items.item_description: If you wish to grasp the finer points of Dhreg Cult dogma, you must wear the proper gear for rending the tracts into ribbons.

items.name: Viridus Leggings
items.item_description: Girded in madness, these leggings defy meaning.

items.name: Viridus Spine
items.item_description: A surfeit of arcane certainty may lead to exquisite eruptions. While painful, these excrescences mark one who has mastered the ultimate lore.

items.name: Battery of the Crested Cannoneer
items.item_description:
For when cannons and pistols, flame and swords have failed.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Izoku
items.item_description: Juggernaut never weeps for what he has lost. Implacable, he purges his grief in pursuit of honor.

items.name: Diffusal Lance
items.item_description: One lance is especially prized by all of Azwraith's phantoms.

items.name: Enchanted Manglewood Staff
items.item_description: A limb hewn from the gnarliest tree in the Manglewood Forest.

items.name: Mistral Braid
items.item_description: The wind that gently tousles her locks, gives unmatched flight to Windranger's arrows.

items.name: Stoneshard Crown
items.item_description: As the molten earth cooled, its will was manifested in the Stoneshard Crown; but there was no coronation until Earthshaker's arrival.

items.name: Stoneshard Bracers
items.item_description: Earthshaker's might is bound in majesty.

items.name: Core of Stoneshard Majesty
items.item_description: Basaltic columns, gathered like limbs of the earth, all presided over by the glowering face of a forgotten ancestor.

items.name: Stoneshard Belt
items.item_description: Shards of stone, gathered from a bottomless quarry, gird Earthshaker's loins.

items.name: Arc of Manta - Off-Hand
items.item_description: A blade incised with runes that sow confusion and discord among the enemy.

items.name: Arc of Manta
items.item_description: A blade incised with runes that sow confusion and discord among the enemy.

items.name: Star of Silence
items.item_description: Forged of the ore at a dead star's heart, in a corner of the universe that has never known sound.

items.name: Mistblade
items.item_description: Forged in the Font of Avernus, and filled with a dark thirst.

items.name: Armblade of the Chiseled Guard
items.item_description: Fashioned from an ax of the Chiseled Guard, this blade serves as shield and side arm.

items.name: Greathelm of the Chiseled Guard
items.item_description: Though what or who they once held safe has long since passed, the armor of the Chiseled Guard remains.

items.name: Blade of the Chiseled Guard
items.item_description: The blade of the Chiseled Guard is said carry the weight of ten men.

items.name: Pauldron of the Chiseled Guard
items.item_description: A heavy counterweight to a heavy blade.

items.name: Tassets of the Chiseled Guard
items.item_description: Though it weighs as much an entire suit of armor, this piece is actually the lightest piece among the arms of the Chiseled Guard.

items.name: Luminous Edge
items.item_description: Much like Sven himself, a blade with a code of its own, which cares not what other swords may be doing.

items.name: Style of the Occult Protector
items.item_description: A fashion for those who vow to protect the mysteries.

items.name: Emerald Frenzy Spikes
items.item_description: Show those spikes off in style!

items.name: Emerald Frenzy Flail
items.item_description: Make 'em see green before they're soaked in red!

items.name: Emerald Frenzy Helmet
items.item_description: A prickly back might be great for a fight, but down in an emerald mine you'll need a hard head too.

items.name: Emerald Frenzy Glove
items.item_description: Good for mining. Great for punching.

items.name: Emerald Frenzy Amulet
items.item_description: You know how it goes: you meet some people who like to fight, you fight them, and you keep their best bits for yourself!

items.name: Obsidian Golem
items.item_description: From cooling lava stalks a burning form.

items.name: Shreds from the Gloom
items.item_description: Remnant shreds of a fashion from ages long gone past, returned from the nether.

items.name: Beard of the Woodland Outcast
items.item_description: From grove to grove did the prophet wander, and so his beard grew as wild as he.

items.name: Stature of the Woodland Outcast
items.item_description: Ever in bloom are the horns of the wandering prophet.

items.name: Pack of the Woodland Outcast
items.item_description: Never to plant his roots, always to wander the wilds.

items.name: Pride of the Woodland Outcast
items.item_description: Of gnarled branch was made a tool for travel, and in time, a tool for battle.

items.name: Petals of the Woodland Outcast
items.item_description: As ages spent and seasons changed the leaves gathered upon his shoulder, returned to flourishing life.

items.name: Oak of the Woodland Outcast
items.item_description: Born of seed and sun, the Prophet wandered the lands in search of glen and grove in need of aid.

items.name: Kraken's Bane
items.item_description: Created to cleanse the sea of its greatest scourge, this fearsome harpoon is now used against those who once dared wield it.

items.name: Laments of the Dead
items.item_description: Forged by a necromantic smith, on whose anvil tortured souls were hammered into obedience, it is Rotund'jere's pleasure to make sure this deadly scythe fulfills its only wish: to reap the souls of the living.

items.name: Grievous Grapnel
items.item_description: There's no time for grappling with your conscience when your dinner is getting away.

items.name: Ashborn Horns
items.item_description: Some say all great things must burn so that they can be reborn. But for Pugna, the first step is the only one worth caring about.

items.name: Lovebear
items.item_description:
The most important member of any team!

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Staff of Infernal Chaos
items.item_description: A Dreadwood staff  engraved with hellish runes to confine a spirit from the Outer Hells inside it.

items.name: Frozen Stein of the Bar Brawler
items.item_name: Frozen Stein of the Bar Brawler
items.item_description: There's always time for a frosty mug!

items.name: Plunder of the High Seas
items.item_description: Pillage with plunder!

items.name: Meadow's Mercy
items.item_description: Though the forest itself may be neutral, this spear will bring a swift end to those who dare disturb the creatures who call it home.

items.name: Eye of Niuhi
items.item_description: Engrained within the beaten blade of the fisherman who first slew him lies the eye of Niuhi, a monster from the deep, long defeated but not forgotten.

items.name: Shadow Brand
items.item_description: Such a blade will sear the stamp of chaos deep into the fabric of order.

items.name: Hare Hunt Rifle
items.item_description: Overkill for a rabbit hunt? You haven't seen these particular rabbits.

items.name: Hare Hunt Sleeves
items.item_description: Richly ornate protection for Sniper's forearms when he creeps through shady cover, as snipers do.

items.name: Hare Hunt Shoulders
items.item_description: What's that? I can't hear you. There's a lit fuse hissing in my ear.

items.name: Hare Hunt Cape
items.item_description: A cape as golden as the autumn woods through which he stalks his tremulous prey.

items.name: Hare Hunt Hat
items.item_description: A furry woodland pelt is a perfect pate protector.

items.name: Trident of the Deep One
items.item_description: Once the temple's caryatids looked out upon a mountain fastness, but those lofty peaks have long since slumped beneath the waves. No one remembers who carved those guardian figures, or even what that nation called itself. And the statue merely scowled a little when Slardar slipped the ancient trident free of its barnacle-encrusted paws.

items.name: Sturdy Bracers of the Exiled Ronin
items.item_name: Sturdy Bracers of the Exiled Ronin
items.item_description: To stand strong and steadfast alone against the world.. with no master to guide him.

items.name: Fire of the Exiled Ronin
items.item_description: The flames of the Ronin burn hot against all who oppose him.

items.name: Burden of the Exiled Ronin
items.item_description: Upon Juggernaut's exile, a mask was bestowed upon his neck that would impart he was indeed a Ronin without a master.

items.name: Vestments of the Exiled Ronin
items.item_description: When one trusty sword is not enough. An exile must always be prepared.

items.name: Ancient Armor Arms
items.item_description: Water finds its perfect form in Morphling's grip.

items.name: Ancient Armor Back
items.item_description: A shield that barely skims the surface of Morphling's power.

items.name: Ancient Armor Breastplates
items.item_description: Injury added to insult, there is nothing worse than being struck full on by Morphling when he wears these plates.

items.name: Ancient Armor Helmet
items.item_description: Watery thoughts can scarcely be contained.

items.name: Ancient Armor Shoulder Shields
items.item_description: The elements align themselves to enhance an ancient strength.

items.name: Fallen Sword
items.item_description: The sword that burns and is not consumed.

items.name: Cloud Forged Great Bracers
items.item_description: Solid bracers with a wide surace area designed to block a wide variety of attacks.

items.name: Tail of Fury
items.item_description: Poets will tell the tale of the great fury of Barathrum.

items.name: Bracers of Fury
items.item_description: These arm  guards protect against the occasional wayward strike of your own flail.

items.name: Belt of Fury
items.item_description: Proving pants are superfluous, if your belt is this powerful.

items.name: Mask of Fury
items.item_description: Your face is masked but your fury won't be.

items.name: Pauldrons of Fury
items.item_description: Upon your broad shoulders, the weight of the war rests.

items.name: Spirit Crusher
items.item_description: Your enemy's spirits will be crushed by the sight of this dread weapon.

items.name: Cloud Forged Great Girdle
items.item_description: Strips of cloth gilded with mithril and fastened to a sturdy girdle. The trail of this belt is spoken of among foot soldiers who gaze to the sky above to see Dragonus fly through the clouds.

items.name: Cloud Forged Great Helm
items.item_description: This ornate helm was once seen worn by royal guards of the nest.

items.name: Cloud Forged Great Mantle
items.item_description: This mantle dons a masterful shape to deflect blades but its deeper enchantments protect from sorcery as well.

items.name: Cloud Forged Great Wings
items.item_description: Arcane energy resonates across the raven-like feathers of these magic infused wings.

items.name: Hand of Hell's Ambassador
items.item_description: Enemies cower when he raises this horrific hand, but friends merely return the greeting.

items.name: Mantle of Hell's Ambassador
items.item_description: Suggestive of the robes of office of some infernal dignitary, the cape was an honorific bestowed on Lion by a grateful demon populace.

items.name: Epaulets of Hell's Ambassador
items.item_description: Shoulderpieces too evil to reside in Hell a moment longer. Lion was only too happy to spare them from the Pit.

items.name: Strifemaul of Hell's Ambassador
items.item_description: He who speaks for Hell may carry the Strifemaul to further emphasize the important points of his argument.

items.name: Admiral's Foraged Cap
items.item_description: A cap found washed up on a Keenish shore, shortly before Kunkka's arrival there.

items.name: Admiral's Stash
items.item_description: The keys that hang from this belt are said to unlock the gates of the Keen capital, the prisons of his fleet, countless treasure chests that lie inside the hull of his majestic ship "Mighty Leviathan" ... and terrifying secrets that lie deep at the bottom of the sea.

items.name: Claddish Gauntlets
items.item_description: The only piece of equipment left on Kunkka after he washed up on a Keen shore.

items.name: Claddish Guard
items.item_description: A high collar keeps salty waters and harsh weather from marring Kunkka's visage, while heavy shoulder-plates have deflected many a tooth and claw belonging to such abominations as lurk in the murky waters.

items.name: Claddish Hightops
items.item_description: These steel toe-guards are effective at fending off sea monsters, as well as punishing booties of lazy Keen sailors.

items.name: Neptunian Sabre
items.item_description: It is said that Kunkka compelled Keen artisans to make this sabre from the salvage of vanquished Cataract Demons that were washed upon the shores of Keen homelands. It is speculated that he split the sea in half with it to locate Maelrawn the Tentacular and sever one of Its tentacles as a testament of his triumph against the Demons of Cataract. Wielding it with brute force and sea-hardened will, he now splits apart his enemies in torrents of sea blue and crimson red.

items.name: Admiral's Salty Shawl
items.item_description: A cape made from the skin of a Cataract Demon, and dyed in the colors of the Claddish Navy, Kunkka wears it to fend off any wicked creature that dares lunge at him.

items.name: Ye Olde Pipe
items.item_description: An old pipe Kunkka plucked from a tidepool after being shipwrecked, the old seadog claims it brings him fortune and good luck, and thus never ever takes it from his scurvy-ridden mouth.

items.name: Faulds of the Gwimyeon Warrior
items.item_description: Speed is always the warrior's ally.

items.name: Gwimyeon
items.item_description: The fiercest face often wins the fiercest battles.

items.name: Juljae Sword
items.item_description: One must always train, must always study, must always struggle in order to forge a path to victory.

items.name: Pauldrons of the Gwimyeon Warrior
items.item_description: To truly conquer a foe, one must best both stem and root.

items.name: Bracers of the Gwimyeon Warrior
items.item_description: One must never neglect the protection of one's swordhand.

items.name: Spring's Lilium Crown
items.item_description: For creatures of the forest, a crown of flowers is more precious than any jewels.

items.name: Pack of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_name: Pack of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_description: A necessity for traveling light across a hostile waste which offers nothing in the way of sustenance or shelter.

items.name: Pads of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_name: Pads of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_description: Relentless sun, scouring winds and the enemy's desperate slashes--these pads are proof against all.

items.name: Cowl of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_name: Cowl of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_description: The hunter hides his face for various reasons, but in the desert wastes the sun is enemy enough.

items.name: Blade of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_name: Blade of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_description: To keep the sands well-named, this blade waits at the ready.

items.name: Shuriken of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_name: Shuriken of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_description: Flying edges bite, and the sand is christened anew.

items.name: Pike of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_name: Pike of the Blood Stained Sands
items.item_description: Bounty Hunter's pike shares a thirst for blood with the arid sands. Whatever it drops will be drunken greedily.

items.name: Cuffs of the Iron Will
items.item_description: From planes beyond and essence untold charges a force to end all.

items.name: Winter Solstice Fashion
items.item_description: Furred in the down of glacial tusk-foxes, this scarf will keep you warm and looking good in the coldest of snowstorms.

items.name: Strap of the Iron Will
items.item_description: None may challenge the breaker's will.

items.name: Horns of the Iron Will
items.item_description: Upon otherworldly horns are fiend and foe gored.

items.name: Mantle of the Iron Will
items.item_description: Against his shoulders does the world shatter.

items.name: Tail of the Iron Will
items.item_description: Sweep from plane to plane.

items.name: Arcane Shield
items.item_description: Charged with sunlight, and with the brighter glare of Invoker's mind, these proud shoulders show every sign they were fashioned by the same powers that forged the sun.

items.name: Arcane Fist
items.item_description: The hand of righteous power will never clench into a fist without good cause.

items.name: Arcane Sight
items.item_description: Emblazoned with the crest of the Scion of the Sun, Invoker wears his mastery of Exort like a crown.

items.name: Arcane Drapings
items.item_description: A tattered, faded cape--it burst to brilliant life, showing its true form once Invoker put it on.

items.name: Formed Alloy Apron
items.item_description:
If you're going bring in a dragon to help you mix alloys you'd best become fireproof!
