These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Formed Alloy Wristplates
items.item_description:
Never underestimate the usefulness of an angry dragon's flamegland when designing new metals!

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Formed Alloy Flask
items.item_description:
Keeping a splash of dragon drool on hand is never a bad idea, assuming you can find the right mix of alloys to store it!

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Formed Alloy Goggles
items.item_description:
A shadeglass eyepiece is a perfect addition to any laboratory.

items.name: Curse of the Highborn
items.item_description: The split and scarred remains of the queen's crown is sewn into the fabric.

items.name: Eki Bukaw Bracers
items.item_description: Forged by your ancestors, these bracers of Eki Bukaw have no like in all the contested lands.

items.name: Records of the Eki Bukaw
items.item_description: Within these sacred records are inscribed all the secrets of the great gone by.

items.name: Auspice of Iczoxtotec
items.item_description: Iczoxtotec, the Herald of Blood, is the great bird of prey of the Flayed Ones, endlessly soaring through the skies in search of sacrifices for its masters. When the battlefields run red with blood, the skies darken and Iczoxtotec is drawn to the carnage.

items.name: Eki Bukaw Wand - Off-Hand
items.item_description: The wand of Eki Bukaw was once thought to be only legend.  But now it is yours to wield, and with it, great power.

items.name: Eki Bukaw Wand
items.item_description: The wand of Eki Bukaw was once thought to be only legend.  But now it is yours to wield, and with it, great power.

items.name: Belt of the Scarlet Raven
items.item_description: When the Feathered One flies, the Flayed Twins smile.

items.name: Gauntlets of the Scarlet Raven
items.item_description: Bound by the Blood Oath, yet free to fly.

items.name: Fiery Ward of Eki Bukaw
items.item_description: With this fiery ward, no secrets are safe, no location hidden, no weakness unexposed.

items.name: Necklace of Scarlet Raven
items.item_description: The sacred bird wheels above the altar of the Flayed Twins.

items.name: Talon of the Scarlet Raven
items.item_description: One talon to open the rivers of blood.

items.name: Coat of the Scarlet Raven
items.item_description: Fly from this raven or die where you stand. In the end, it's all the same.

items.name: Hood of the Scarlet Raven
items.item_description: Fed on quivering heart-meat, the raven's inhuman eyes hum with scarlet hunger.

items.name: Talon of the Scarlet Raven - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Talon of the Scarlet Raven - Off-Hand
items.item_description: One talon to hold his victims pinned fast.

items.name: Steelweb Shell
items.item_description: Those who worshipped the spiders of Mount Pyrotheos found the snarling heat below the caldera perfectly suited to forging armor for their insatiable queen.

items.name: Steelweb Cuirass
items.item_description: Nothing now remains of those who once worshipped the spider queen of Mount Pyrotheos, save trinkets and arms long lost within the endless web.

items.name: Steelweb Countenance
items.item_description: For she of boundless hunger was forged this mask, that her many eyes may never come to harm.

items.name: Steelweb Sheaths
items.item_description: There are those who would worship the Broodmother and her ilk, and cover them with gifts before throwing themselves to the webs to be devoured.

items.name: Tsunami Blade
items.item_description: Acquired after the ferocious battle of Port Mignin, this enchanted blade now belongs to Kunkka.

items.name: Blade of Burning Turmoil
items.item_description: Forged in the heat of a dying star.

items.name: Horns of Burning Turmoil
items.item_description: From realms beyond mortal knowledge rides forth a heaving darkness.

items.name: Enmity
items.item_description: Its strides are hatred, its bray a judgment, its gallop the march of destruction.

items.name: Shield of Burning Turmoil
items.item_description: Cooled in the black nether between worlds, its core still bends and burns.

items.name: Mantle of Burning Turmoil
items.item_description: Within the astral turmoil, heat bends and matter swirls.

items.name: Thorns of the Highborn
items.item_description: Svelte and sturdy are the horns of the highborn.

items.name: Wrath of the Highborn
items.item_description: Smuggled out by servants as the Tahlin dynasty fell, these ornate blades are finally back in royal hands.

items.name: Temper of the Highborn - Off-Hand
items.item_description: Smuggled out by servants as the Tahlin dynasty fell, these ornate blades are finally back in royal hands.

items.name: Burden of the Highborn
items.item_description: To restore his family's rule, and to govern those of his kingdom; these are the burdens Riki strives toward.

items.name: Whisk of the Highborn
items.item_description: Often made to be soft and luxuriant, a highborn's tail is commonly used to display its owner's status in society.

items.name: Cloth of the Clergy Ascetic
items.item_description: What clergy approved this lurid wrap and thought it suitable for an ascetic lifestyle? None survive to justify their decision.

items.name: Reprieve of the Clergy Ascetic - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Reprieve of the Clergy Ascetic - Off-Hand
items.item_description: Earthly desires, passions and possessions are burdens from which Antimage can readily liberate you.

items.name: Adornment of the Clergy Ascetic
items.item_description: It seems paradoxical that an ascetic would seek adornment, but Antimage has never followed trends.

items.name: Reprieve of the Clergy Ascetic
items.item_description: Earthly desires, passions and possessions are burdens from which Antimage can readily liberate you.

items.name: Guard of the Clergy Ascetic
items.item_description: The rightmost shoulder of Antimage: Righter by far than thou!

items.name: Armor of the Enlightened
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Cape of the Enlightened
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Bracers of the Silent Guardian
items.item_description: These bracers protect their wearer from the ravages battle.

items.name: Shift of the Silent Guardian
items.item_description: Cloaked in Silence, and also in this stylish shift.

items.name: Shield of the Silent Guardian
items.item_description: Sometimes a lack of magic is the greatest magic of all.  But for those times when it isn't, this shield might help.

items.name: Pauldron of the Silent Guardian
items.item_description: Crafted by ancient artisans, these pauldrons protect Silencer from those who would do him harm.

items.name: Blade of the Silent Guardian
items.item_description: They'll never hear it coming.

items.name: Thorned Abdomen of Malice
items.item_description: A necessary camouflage in the Thorny Wastes where she stalks a particular prey required to nourish her young.

items.name: Thorned Skitterers of Despite
items.item_description: Even outside the Thorny Wastes, Broodmother affects the look--as much because it appeals to her eyes as for its defensive properties.

items.name: Helm of the Silent Guardian
items.item_description: A quiet, protected mind leads to a quick blade.

items.name: Visage of Eki Bukaw
items.item_description: The Visage of the Eki Bukaw will be the last thing your enemies see before they cross the final hill into the great gone by.

items.name: Bracers of the Clergy Ascetic
items.item_description: A constant reminder of the world he left behind when he struck off on the ascetic's path.

items.name: Cloud Forged Great Staff
items.item_description: A shard of cloud crystal inlaid with a strip of skywrath gold there is no finer conductor for sorcery than this great staff.

items.name: Armlets of Teardrop Ice
items.item_description: Legends tell of twelve lost gems, teardrops that glow of glacial ice, imbued with a chill so deep that even the desert sands were turned to tundra.

items.name: Belt of Teardrop Ice
items.item_description: The largest of the legendary teardrop gems shines with the glow of eternal glaciers.

items.name: Pauldron of Teardrop Ice
items.item_description: Of the twelve legendary teardrop gems, eight were shattered, creating a vast tundra where once stood a burning waste.

items.name: Spear of Teardrop Ice
items.item_description: The two teardrop gems pressed into the haft ensure the spear's icy edge never thaws.

items.name: Clergy Warhammer
items.item_description: When you are Omniknight's hammer, every opponent resembles a nail.

items.name: Shattered Destroyer
items.item_description: From the shards of numerous broken enemies, a weapon to be borne by one King alone.

items.name: Mattock of Distortion
items.item_description: One blow of this mighty mallet, and waves of time-warping distortion spread to erase his enemies from existence.

items.name: Aethereal Crescent Wand
items.item_description: For a Skywrath, schooled in aethereal mastery, the subtler powers of nature are more tangible and easier to capture in the form of a wand.

items.name: Phantom's Reaper
items.item_description: If you have done nothing to anger the Font of Avernus, then you should have nothing to fear when Abaddon rides out on his errands of correction.

items.name: The Savage Orchid
items.item_description: A garnet rod constructed from the essence of a fire demon.

items.name: Piercing Umbrage
items.item_description: Be careful when you speak ill of Riki, for although unseen, he may well be within earshot. And he has been known to take umbrage.

items.name: Piercing Umbrage - Off-Hand
items.item_description: Be careful when you speak ill of Riki, for although unseen, he may well be within earshot. And he has been known to take umbrage.

items.name: The Celestial Bane
items.item_description: This visage, so terrifying to mundane enemies, is a face of comfort and reassurance to those conceived and reared above the Outworld.

items.name: Carapace of the Chosen Larva
items.item_description: Molted over the course of seven seasons by the slow administration of special alchemicals, this carapace is hardened against both blade and spell.

items.name: Helmet of the Chosen Larva
items.item_description: Beneath this ornate helmet of hardened chitin rages a mind unlike any other in the insect world--a cold intelligence bent on the destruction of the chosen target.

items.name: Stinger of the Chosen Larva
items.item_description: There are worse deaths than the sting of the chosen larva.  Theoretically.  You do not want this creature to sting you.

items.name: Pincers of the Chosen Larva
items.item_description: The only part of this assassin not grown naturally, these steel blades are screwed directly into the tough chitin at the ends of his killing limbs.

items.name: Formed Alloy Blades
items.item_description:
Invaluable and nigh indestructible, it can take up to fourteen months to mix materials to concoct just one pound of shadeglass.

items.name: Gwanji the Thunder Lizard
items.item_description: Long thought extinct, the deadly Gwanji is a living relic from a bygone age.

items.name: Vingspan
items.item_description: Ever in search of new thrills, the Rider commandeered an unlikely steed in a faraway land, with nothing but grit and persuasive Garlic breath.

items.name: Chronoptic Crown
items.item_description: Heavy is the head that wears this crown.

items.name: Flail of the Iron Will
items.item_description: Shimmering with an elder power, one swing is enough to dim even the stoutest heart.

items.name: Bramblehorn
items.item_description: She who rides a tiger is afraid to dismount.

items.name: Windweave Headband
items.item_description: A headband of finest silk.

items.name: The Elegant Stroke
items.item_description: Forged more than a thousand years ago by the master bladesmith Sabasteen, this beautiful sword has long proven the deadliest stroke can also be the most elegant.

items.name: Blade of Misery
items.item_description: A real assassin needs more than one weapon to defend herself.  Even her blade has blades.

items.name: Slashing Quickslicer - Off-Hand

items.item_description:
A skilled shifter and sorcerer, Throsho often took a demon's form to intimidate those who lived within his realm. Those frightened by his appearance grew in time to worship him, often bringing him ornamental tithes.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Hood of the Cruel Magician
items.item_description:
What mind muses within the shadows? Sometimes mystery itself can be cruelty.

items.name: Pauldron of the Warrior's Retribution
items.item_description: The rogue shoulders more than his share of grief and retribution.

items.name: Robe of the Cruel Magician
items.item_description:
To consort with the shades, one should dress appropriately.

items.name: Sword of the Warrior's Retribution
items.item_description: A weapon that once belonged to Sven's father, it was years before the son discovered its transformative properties.

items.name: Belt of the Warrior's Retribution
items.item_description: It's payback...in the form of a belt.

items.name: Mantle of the Cruel Magician
items.item_description:
The quest for knowledge oft leads down dark paths.

items.name: Cape of the Warrior's Retribution
items.item_description: Weatherproof, waterproof, bloodproof.

items.name: Staff of the Cruel Magician
items.item_description:
Through the darkest channels travel the most powerful sorceries.

items.name: Gauntlet of the Warrior's Retribution
items.item_description: Grip a sword or the throat of an enemy--it's all the same to Sven.

items.name: Helm of the Warrior's Retribution
items.item_description: Beneath his helm, Sven's thoughts are hidden. But the image he presents to the world may change like the weather.

items.name: Belt of the Gleaming Seal
items.item_description:
Whispered tales speak of death made flesh, an ironclad shape with a blade of crescent light.

items.name: Cape of the Gleaming Seal
items.item_description:
A sweep of movement, a shift of dark leather, are all that the dead will have time to see.

items.name: Brooch of the Gleaming Seal
items.item_description:
Above a pallid brow do death's feathers roost.

items.name: Ornaments of the Gleaming Seal
items.item_description:
Though they shine by moonlight, in truth the blades serve to draw the eye away from death's true instrument.

items.name: The Gleaming Seal
items.item_description:
With but a flash, a final fate is sealed.

items.name: Barrier Shard Axe
items.item_description: Chipped from a glacier off the Barrier, this axe brings out the Tusk's most brutal fighting spirit.

items.name: Antennae of the Master Weaver
items.item_description: Always alert for the slightest variations in the cosmic flux.

items.name: Sabatons of the Crested Cannoneer
items.item_description:
Below decks, behind a line of artillery primed to fire, sure footing is essential.

items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Roshan Hunter Back
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Roshan Hunter Belt
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Roshan Hunter Head
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Gloves of the Crested Cannoneer
items.item_description:
A gauntlet for the sword hand, a mitt to grip the rum!

items.name: Plume of the Crested Cannoneer
items.item_description:
The captain of a Claddish cannon crew wears a plume of dyed horsehair to make their authority evident.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: Mantle of the Crested Cannoneer
items.item_description:
Upon the shoulders of the cannoneer lie the fate of their fleet and fellows.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

items.name: The Second Disciple's Bastion
items.item_description: Sometimes a bounty does not need to be collected immediately if the hunter believes there is more to gain on a job. Gondar enlists in the army of the infidel in order to obtain sturdy gear and learn the stolen secrets of Soruq that have been bestowed upon the undeserving army.

items.name: The Second Disciple's Veil
items.item_description: With the power imbued in the veil of the second disciple, Gondar learned a rare and useful technique passed down from his old master. With the sigil of the enchanted blade, the hunter can feel a great power that was nearly lost to the filthy traitor.

items.name: The Second Disciple's Dagger
items.item_description: Stolen from the betrayer himself, Gondar used this weapon to slit the throat of the deceitful war general and seal the fate of the army founded on infidelity.

items.name: The Second Disciple's Chakram
items.item_description: Carried upon his back, this weapon serves as both defense and offense on the field of battle.

items.name: The Second Disciple's Blade
items.item_description: This blade, fashioned of salvaged equipment from the battlefield, serves as a reminder to both Gondar and his enemies of what happens to those who betray sacred trusts.

items.name: Darkstar the Mistforged
items.item_description: This ancestral blade of House Avernus was cast into the Font, to be forged anew. What emerged was an amalgam of steel, and mist, that feasts upon the souls of its foes.

items.name: Netherax, Nightmare of the Mist
items.item_description: When the Font anointed Abaddon with its power, it also conjured up a creature, equally terrifying, for its champion to ride into battle.

items.name: The Second Disciple's Satchel
items.item_description: Gondar carries his important materials and implements in his satchel, always prepared for future hunts.

items.name: Hellfire Edge
items.item_description: Seared, hacked, and trampled. No indignity is too small to be meted out by Chaos Knight and his steed.

items.name: Slicer of the Depths
items.item_description: A shiv assembled from contraband gems. Better not ask how Slark kept it concealed in Dark Reef Prison.

items.name: Taunt: It's in the Bag
items.item_description:
Express your confidence to the enemy team. Surely nothing could possibly go wrong...

This taunt can be equipped as an action item and used with any hero.

items.name: Toxic Gaze
items.item_description: May cause blindness.

items.name: Drodo the Druffin
items.item_description: Discovered on an island in the Samareen Sea, this species of delicious dragon has been all but wiped out by hungry sailors.  Druffins lack the sense that nature gives most creatures, but their limitless trust makes them good couriers in the thick of battle.

items.name: Murrissey the Smeevil
items.item_description: It is rare to find a smeevil far from the warmth of the forge to which it's bound, for they thrive on the affectionate cuffings and curses of their sworn smith. But the lure of a free tortoiceros ride compelled the smeevil Murrissey to break every oath...

items.name: Lockjaw the Boxhound
items.item_description: Most boxhounds you're likely to come across would sooner eat you just for touching them, but all this little guy ever wants to do is play fetch.  His master never came home from battle, so if Lockjaw follows you home you should probably keep him.

items.name: Slayer's Glare
items.item_description: Why light a fire if you can't watch it burn?

items.name: Ramnaught of Underwool
items.item_description: The beasts of Underwool are terrible bringers of death and destruction, demons of shadow afflicted by a black wizard's curse that has ensured they are forever cute and fluffy.

items.name: Announcer: Dr. Kleiner
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the sharp mind of science's Dr. Kleiner.

items.name: Enduring War Dog
items.item_description: A dog well equipped to follow its master into war. This beast has witnessed many terrible deeds and grand victories. It hides stoic judgment beneath a painted mask of fine birch.

items.name: Nightmare Beacon
items.item_description: The terrors of battle hold many dark secrets.

items.name: Trusty Mountain Yak
items.item_description: This trusty Yak bears a thrice-blessed Mask of Duty, as is requred of all those noble beasts who might serve in battle.

items.name: Fearless Badger
items.item_description: Of all the creatures of the forest, the badger makes perhaps the finest courier. Fearless and quick, it bends its will to none save those who have earned its trust.

items.name: Announcer: Juggernaut
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the carefully chosen words of the traveling warrior, Juggernaut.

items.name: Mega-Kills: Juggernaut
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the enthusiastic shouts of the traveling warrior, Juggernaut.

items.name: Announcer: Nature's Prophet
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the stern voice of Nature's Prophet.

items.name: Mega-Kills: Nature's Prophet
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the wild cries of Nature's Prophet.

items.name: Stumpy - Nature's Attendant
items.item_description: Stumpy isn't very good in battle, but he's more than happy to haul around your loot and he's always there when you need him.

items.name: Dolfrat and Roshinante
items.item_description: "How did I get here?" Such words of power are commonly heard from Dolfrat the Wizard, whose magic is so great that even he cannot grasp it. Indeed, his enemies accuse him of having no magical training whatsoever, pointing to the evidence of his most frequent incantation: "Did I do that?" And should you ever spy the mighty Dolfrat flat on his back in the road, you can be sure his trusty steed Roshinante is somewhere nearby--probably galloping at top speed away from a creaky tree or shadow that resembled a demon of nightmarish power.

items.name: Braze the Zonkey
items.item_description: Separated from his herd when disruptions to the traditional migratory route took it through a tesseract, he stands out a bit in this new habitat. But that's all right. Apart from enemy heroes, he has no natural predators!

items.name: Lost Treasure of the Ivory Isles
items.item_name: Lost Treasure of the Ivory Isles
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of the Deep Druids
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of the Red Mist
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Tickled Tegu
items.item_description: A friendly Tegu from the dragon infested Cathauran Wastes. He smiles as if he knows something you do not.

items.name: Mighty Boar
items.item_description: This boar has a crazed look in his eye. Is it distrust? Madness? Or does he just want to eat your tangos.

items.name: Morok's Mechanical Mediary
items.item_description: Don't let its metal form deceive you: this contraption is more magic than machine. Fashioned by the Mad Mage Morok who was far too lazy to carry his own spell books and far too cheap to retain hirlings.

items.name: Speed Demon
items.item_description: This imp has trained all his life for this moment. He is SO ready to go. He will deliver your loot on time or suffer eternal damnation in the sixty-four planes of the Lesser Hells.

items.name: Skip the Delivery Frog
items.item_description: What he lacks in size he makes up for in character.

items.name: Announcer: Storm Spirit
items.item_description: This pack replaces the Default announcer with the boisterous theatrics of Storm Spirit.

items.name: Announcer: The Pirate Cap'n
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the drunken antics of a scurvy-ridden Pirate Captain.

items.name: Mega-Kills: The Pirate Cap'n
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the drunken antics of a scurvy-ridden Pirate Captain.

items.name: Treasure of the Pangolin Guildmasters
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Defense Season 2 War Dog
items.item_description: A special reward for subscribers to The Defense Season 2 tournament.

items.name: Treasure of the Ancestor Spirits
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of the High Tide
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Sithil's Summer Stash
items.item_description: That disreputable scoundrel Sithil has lost a chest of plundered loot! You will need <font color='#9da1a9'>Sithil's Summer Key</font> to open the chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Beware! At the end of <font color='#9da1a9'>July 31, 2012</font> this chest will crumble into useless dust. This chest contains one of several mysterious new items.

items.name: The Defense 2 Chest
items.item_description: A special reward for early subscribers to <font color='#9da1a9'>The Defense Season 2</font> tournament. Included with a key used to open this chest. Thank you for helping us test and improve our tournament features!

items.name: Mega-Kills: Storm Spirit
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the joyful exposition of Storm Spirit.

items.name: Treasure of Profound Mysteries
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Team Pennant: Alliance
items.item_description: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

items.name: Mok
items.item_description: One of the wildest beasts of the escaped menagerie that ran amok during the fall of Slom, this wily mandrill took Mok for his name, thinking the citizenry's cries of warning were a herald of his arrival.  Now he puts his mischievous nature to good use, wading into any chaotic situation in order to bring you what you need.

items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the double-edged wit of Axe.

items.name: Mega-Kills: Axe
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the resonant booms of Axe.

items.name: Treasure of the Rogue Knight
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Timeless Treasure of Claszureme
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of the Wild Claw
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Greevil Egg
items.item_description: A hard, scaled egg that seems to be alive and almost ready to hatch. It hungers for the magical energies contained in Diretide essences. What comes out will be determined by the type and amount of magic the egg consumes.

items.name: Eyeball Fetish
items.item_description: "I like to watch."

items.name: Staff of Faith
items.item_description: Seeing is believing.

items.name: Skywrath Sentinel
items.item_description: Although she may never reach the lofty hights of the Ghastly Eyrie again, Shendelzare still has allies that will grant her assistance when she requires it.

items.name: Greevil
items.item_description: A strange beast infused with magic. Its color, appearance, and abilities are determined by the types of magical essences it was exposed to while still an egg.

items.name: Baby Roshan
items.item_description: He's just a little guy! He doesn't know any better.

items.name: Ghastly Treasure of Diretide
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Diretide Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store.

items.name: Golden Baby Roshan
items.item_description: A rare and glittering trophy awarded to the fastest slayers of Sugar Rush Roshan.

items.name: Eye of the Ozkavosh
items.item_description: Until its fall, none could escape the spying gaze of the First Dominion.

items.name: Blueheart Spotter
items.item_description: Here's eyes in your ice!

items.name: Announcer: Death Prophet
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the haunted tones of Death Prophet.

items.name: Na'Vi's Weaselcrow
items.item_description: Fur and feather, beak and fang, Weaselcrow is just the thing!

items.name: Prismatic Drake
items.item_description: The young Prismatic Drake displays a natural mimicry by which it blends into the mountainous piles of gems that make up its familial hoard. Thus disguised, the tiny and vulnerable young are safe from cave spiders, hoard-thieves and other predators.

items.name: Augury's Guardian
items.item_description: From deep within the mystic woods behind the veil of augury, the guardian watches over and protects its allies.

items.name: Treasure of the Hunted Dragon
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of the Silent Grove
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Cruel Diretide
items.item_description: As tide and temperature turn, life ebbs from the land.  The Diretide has arrived.

items.name: Treasure of the Twins
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Frosty Treasure of Frostivus
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Announcer: Bastion
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the euphemistic keen-eyed wisdom of Bastion's narrator, also known as Rucks.

items.name: Mega-Kills: Bastion
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the smooth worldly tones of Bastion's narrator, also known as Rucks.

items.name: 2012 Polycount Ward
items.item_description: Ward presented to winners of the 2012 Winter Polycount Contest

items.name: Golden Greevil
items.item_description: A reward for slaying a rare loot greevil.

items.name: Deathripper
items.item_description:
A terrifying combination of dark magic and science-gone-wrong, the bestial Deathripper is a boon to its master and a nightmare to all others.

Hailing from the Iron Kingdoms, the Deathripper is a deadly creation of the undead nation of Cryx, as seen in the epic tabletop miniatures game, WARMACHINE. For more information on WARMACHINE, visit www.privateerpress.com

items.name: Treasure of Dark Implements
items.item_description: A darkly gleaming treasure with mysterious contents. You must use a Dark Treasure Key to open this.

items.name: Black Pool Watcher
items.item_description: Silently surveying and plotting the theft of your mana, and your life.

items.name: Cluckles the Brave
items.item_description: Many critters can be trained to ferry tools into battle.  Few will do so while wearing a jetpack!

items.name: Hellgazer
items.item_description: While Warlock is deep in study, his sentry keeps an eye out for Infernal interruptions--as well as more mundane intrusions.

items.name: Radiant Ore
items.item_description: Light pours into the land, blooming resplendent on war-scarred ruins.

items.name: Direstone
items.item_description: The earth cracks in turmoil as the seeds of destruction take root.

items.name: Snows of Frostivus
items.item_description: A chill fills the air as the snows blanket the cold ground.  The time of Frostivus comes.

items.name: Treasure of the Omniscient
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of the Restless Seas
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of Tidal Power
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of the Forbidden Lotus
items.item_description: A strange and fragrant chest. The lock is of an unknown design and the contents are currently a mystery.

items.name: Bottom Watcher
items.item_description: From far below, a dweller of the deeps has been pressed into service at the surface!

items.name: Double Vision
items.item_description: This mascot of the powerful Pyrexae has two heads with which to scout for trouble!

items.name: Wynchell the Wyrmeleon
items.item_description: Is it a clever chameleon pretending to be a powerful Wyrm, or a celebrated Wyrm trying to pass itself off as an anonymous chameleon? Truly, the dimensions have begun to spill into each other, and nothing may be taken for granted. Especially not Wynchell.

items.name: Star Ladder Grillhound
items.item_description: The taming of a grillhound is a tale filled with trials and breakthroughs, and more than a few singed eyebrows.

items.name: Announcer: Tuskar
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with punchy lines from Tusk.

items.name: Treasure of Crystalline Chaos
items.item_description: A heavy chest of alien crystal. The lock is of an unknown design.

items.name: Nimble Ben
items.item_description: Nimble Ben here! And there! And everywhere! Send me where you want me and I'm already there!

items.name: Porcine Princess Penelope
items.item_description: Attention, Your Pink and Portly Highness, your loyal bearer has arrived! Treat him well, for he is very attached to you. In fact, there's really no way to shake him.

items.name: Snowl
items.item_description: The Goddess of the Moon presses many forest creatures into her service.  Always crafty, ever vigilant, little Snowl would give his all to aid the guardians of the Nightsilver.

items.name: Treasure of the Cursed Wood
items.item_description: A gnarled chest formed of a dark, still-living wood. The lock glows with cursed runes.

items.name: Treasure of Rarities
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Captain Bamboo
items.item_description: Not just a Panda, He's a Captain!

items.name: Treasure of the Shaper Divine
items.item_description: A chest of magical items created by the community contributor Anuxi.

items.name: Snelfret the Snail
items.item_description: The original rebel snail, Snelfret refused to conform to a social order that enforced lethargy, a world that told him he must not move too fast. So he loaded up his shell and headed for more dynamic climes, determined to redefine the meaning of snail's pace.

items.name: Inky the Hexapus
items.item_description: Inky the hexapus was fished from the waters of the Horn of Despair and pressed into service by a fleet of marauding pirates, carrying messages to and fro between ships.

items.name: The Llama Llama
items.item_description: The Llama Llama courier... with a courier THIS good, you name him TWICE!   "Fleet of Foots" and "Service with a Smile!" ... What more can you ask for?

items.name: Kupu the Metamorpher
items.item_description: All hail Kupu the Metamorpher!  Honest and forthright, Kupu with delivery your items in a most timely fashion.  Steadfast!

items.name: Deepest Depths
items.item_description: Within the coldest depths one must be clever and adaptable, or become food for one that is.

items.name: Smeevil
items.item_description: Tis said among artisan and warrior alike that there is no finer servant than a trusty smeevil.  However, a hero who chooses a smeevil as their courier may soon find these clever critters taking new forms in order to gain assistants of their own. Inspired by the great battles they bear witness to, a smeevil may become emboldened to press ever more exotic beasts to their cause.

items.name: Treasure of the Malignant Amanita
items.item_description: A chest that seems mildly poisonous to the touch. The contents are unknown.

items.name: Empowered
items.item_description:
The thrum of war, 
	the stomp of hooves, 
	the bloodstained earth, 
	grim forces move.

items.name: Tempest Wing
items.item_description: Those who fail the skies face nothing but a very long fall.

items.name: Mega-Kills: Pyrion Flax
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the unique and unruly humor of Dota 2 satirist Pyrion Flax.

items.name: Frozen Touch
items.item_description: There is cold wisdom in the core of winter.

items.name: Malice
items.item_description: Few things confer courage like the power of malice.

items.name: Nature
items.item_description: In the verdant spring grows deep-rooted strength.

items.name: Driftwood
items.item_description: Upon a sandy shore lie the tools of victory.

items.name: Gear Tooth
items.item_description: Ingenuity powers the machinery of war.

items.name: A Dire Gaze
items.item_description: Many things may lie hidden among the rocks and magma.

items.name: Announcer: Pyrion Flax
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the unique and unruly humor of Dota 2 satirist Pyrion Flax.

items.name: Stone Ruin
items.item_description:
Beware the chaos of ages past.
	
	Included with Premier League Season 5 pass.

items.name: Powered Star
items.item_description:
With power comes victory.
	
	Included with Star Series Season VI pass..

items.name: Fezzle-Feez the Magic Carpet Smeevil
items.item_description: Fezzle-Feez, like most smeevils, has no floor on which to spread his magic carpet, therefore he unrolls it in mid-air.

items.name: Team Pennant: Dignitas
items.item_description: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

items.name: Valor
items.item_description: With courage comes glory. With glory comes immortality.

items.name: Maximilian the Beetlebear
items.item_description: High on the steppes of Druud, stormcrafters are known to press beasts of burden into their service.  Rare though is the stormcrafter who dares try and control the pugnacious steambear.  That the young bear Maximilian now travels unaccompanied is proof that the domestication process did not go well.  For the stormcrafter.

items.name: Shagbark
items.item_description: Shagbark is a trusty forest familiar who lives for the thrill of delivery. Fond of secrets and artifacts, he hopes you'll never finish farming.

items.name: Yonex's Rage
items.item_description: In the blood-mists of the fiercest of battles, the dragon finds its true calling... the call of Invictus Gaming.

items.name: El Gato
items.item_description:
Fiercely determined, ever courageous, and always clever, not even the mighty Roshan may frighten El Gato from his mission.

El Gato will level up as you watch games that include casters from the Beyond The Summit team.

items.name: Itsy
items.item_description: Not so itsy, say you? Her enormous elder siblings click their mandibles and roll their many eyes at their sister's puny proportions. To prove her worth, this fleet-footed spiderling will eagerly scuttle to your service and weave her web around your heart!

items.name: Elder Bark
items.item_description: The seasons pass, and strength holds true.

items.name: Team Pennant: Liquid
items.item_description: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

items.name: Cyril the Syrmeleon
items.item_description: The shy syrmeleon of the southern isles are rarely ones to travel abroad, or find themselves in a battle, or hitch a ride on an elder drakefly.

items.name: Jungle Ruin
items.item_description: There are tales hidden deep in the jungle dark.

items.name: Smeevil Treat
items.item_description: A tasty snack used to unlock new Smeevil styles.

items.name: Furnace
items.item_description: As flames rise, power grows.

items.name: Critter Egg
items.item_description: A magical egg used to unlock new Smeevil styles.

items.name: Treasure of Incandescent Wax
items.item_description: A chest that seems to be burning endlessly. The contents are unknown.

items.name: Quirt's Summer Stash
items.item_description: That disreputable scoundrel Quirt has lost a chest of plundered loot! You will need <font color='#9da1a9'>Quirt's Summer Key</font> to open the chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Beware! At the end of <font color='#9da1a9'>September 16, 2013</font> this chest will crumble into useless dust. This chest contains one of several mysterious new items.

items.name: Team Pennant: LGD.Int
items.item_description: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

items.name: Team Pennant: Fnatic
items.item_description: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

items.name: Alphid of Lecaciida
items.item_description: The greenfly colony of Lecaciida had lived and thrived for centuries, inhabiting the trunks of Treants and nourishing themselves on the sap of those ageless giants. Among the hive was a young greenfly named Alphid who had distinguished himself through his agility, swiftness, and curious nature. One the night, he left the colony and set out to find his own destiny, convinced that his exceptional speed and dedication could be put to good use on the battlefield.

items.name: Garran Drywiz and Garactacus
items.item_description: Evil and ill intention are obvious in every gesture of this despicable duo.

items.name: Trapjaw the Boxhound
items.item_description: Within the dungeons of the Severed Keep there sits a treasure hoard long abandoned. Many are the raiders who have set their sights on its wonders, yet only one has ever returned, telling grisly tales of a family of enchanted chests brimming with gold, devouring his friends.

items.name: Tinkbot
items.item_description: Fed up with conventional delivery methods, Tinker set to work on something he felt was a bit more reliable.

items.name: Spell Surveyor
items.item_description: The Spell Surveyor is always on the lookout for spells that might be stolen!

items.name: Blotto and Stick
items.item_description: A former gambler and shyster, the antics of Blotto were once known in every watering hole, gambling den and sleaze pit from here to Slom.  Now on the slow path to reform, he's taken up courier duties to con a bit of extra coin and brought his trusty Stick along for the ride!

items.name: Waldi the Faithful
items.item_description: Orphaned and abandoned on the fringes of the Nightsilver Woods, Waldi was rescued by a reclusive band of rangers and trained in the ways of war. Waldi is often underestimated by his foes, but his unassuming appearance belies his relentless tenacity and unfailing loyalty. He is a worthy courier and companion for the mightiest of warriors, a true dog of duty.

items.name: Iron Cage
items.item_description: Contain and conquer!

items.name: Osky the Ottragon
items.item_description: "Osky! Osky! What a good boy!" He capers and sports, but underneath the playful exterior is an abiding sadness. He misses his siblings.

items.name: Treasure of Champions 2013
items.item_description: You will need an <font color='#9da1a9'>International Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. This chest will disappear at the end of August 12th, 2013. The unusual couriers that may drop from this chest can only be found during the International.

items.name: Mammoth Bait
items.item_description: Once believed extinct, a small population of dwarf Mammoths can still be found on the isolated, northernmost peninsula of Icewrack.  They are shy creatures, not easily baited, but an offered stockpile of nuzzle-fruit will often entice them to approach.

items.name: Cleft Hawk's Call
items.item_description: One among the many striders of Upland Druud, the timid Cleft Hawk makes its home within the many fissures dotting the plains.  The mating call of a Cleft Hawk is said to be as grating as it is unbelievably loud.

items.name: Ocula the Observer
items.item_description: With an eye that big, there's no hiding from Ocula!

items.name: ESWC Diamond
items.item_description: Included with the Electronic Sports World Cup 2013 league pass.

items.name: Curiosity
items.item_description: It cannot be quenched!

items.name: Announcer: Defense Grid
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the upbeat wisdom of Defense Grid's very own General Fletcher.

items.name: Mega-Kills: Defense Grid
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the upbeat wisdom of Defense Grid's very own General Fletcher.

items.name: Dragon Scale
items.item_description: Live by the sword, die by the dragon.

items.name: Aperture Science Wardcore
items.item_description: They can't do it while you're watching.

items.name: Edge Crab Dye
items.item_description: A varying mixture including (but not limited to) sourvine root, dimwine, rummix droppings, powdered deepash, ogrog brew, and butter.  Good for dissolving stone, and dying shells.

items.name: Edge Crab Lure
items.item_description: The dim shores in Dalr's Edge are home to crabs of incredible size.  With the proper lure, one can brought out of hiding.

items.name: Nibbles the Wartoise
items.item_description: A veteran of countless battles spanning untold centuries, Nibbles commands the respect and admiration of even the most hardened warrior.

items.name: LGD's Golden Skipper
items.item_description: The Golden Skipper is a species long-rumored to exist, but rarely seen in the wild.  Among sailors of the high seas, there have been tales passed down through the centuries of a creature whose cuteness is legend, and whose adorableness rises to a level that defies mortal understanding.  It can only be assumed that this is one such rare beast.

items.name: Announcer: GLaDOS
items.item_description: This item replaces the Default announcer with the withering sarcasm and passive-aggressive taunting of Portal's GLaDOS, science fiction's deadliest insult A.I.

items.name: Mega-Kills: GLaDOS
items.item_description: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the withering sarcasm and passive-aggressive taunting of Portal's GLaDOS, science fiction's deadliest insult A.I.

items.name: Underwater
items.item_description: Beneath the waves are powers unknown.

items.name: Arnabus the Fairy Rabbit
items.item_description: Unlike other, less dependable lagomorphs, Arnabus shall never be late with your items. Depend on it!

items.name: Treasure of Rubiline Sheen
items.item_description: Sculpted from the finest Rubiline of Riftshadow, the contents are unknown.

items.name: Recipe: Polymorph Common Items
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of common items and produce a random new common item.

items.name: Dim Forest
items.item_description: What lies forgotten among the leaves and logs?

items.name: Woodchopper
items.item_description: Most would say a log's a log, but when you live downstream from an enchanted forest a log can be so much more!

items.name: Portal
items.item_description: Hello, and welcome to the Aperture Science Cosmetic Data Enclosure.

items.name: Emerald Polycount Collection
items.item_description: All of the items within were crafted by artists of the Polycount community.  You can view the process by which these items were designed, as well as learn to create your own items at http://www.polycount.com

items.name: Golden Treasures
items.item_description: Riches are won on the battlefield.

items.name: Recipe: Augment Common Items
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of specific common items and produce a random new uncommon item.

items.name: Recipe: Augment Uncommon Items
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of specific uncommon items and produce a random new rare item.

items.name: Warding Guise
items.item_description: Exorcise your enemies.

items.name: Recipe: Augment Rare Items
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of specific rare items and produce a random new mythical item.

items.name: Recipe: Craft Exceptional Item
items.item_description: This recipe requires you to collect several specific items to craft an exceptional new item.

items.name: Tremor
items.item_description: War rattles every foundation.

items.name: Ancient Scroll Case
items.item_description: An ancient locked scroll case. Open with a Treasure Key to receive several crafting recipes including a chance of special rare recipes.

items.name: Recipe: Polymorph Rare Items
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of rare items and produce a random new rare item.

items.name: Omen
items.item_description: Ill tidings come unbidden.

items.name: Recipe: Polymorph Mythical Items
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of mythical items and produce a random new mythical item.

items.name: Azuremir
items.item_description: Winding through field and stream, the young dragon Azuremir carries his orbs of soil and stone, ever watchful of the lands around him, and ever helpful to those who call to him.

items.name: Treasure of Heroic Bounty
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Recipe: Polymorph Uncommon Items
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of uncommon items and produce a random new uncommon item.

items.name: Vermilion
items.item_description: Each conflict is unique, like bamboo's bloom in summer's heat.

items.name: Necropolis
items.item_description: Those long buried hold power long forgotten.

items.name: Throe
items.item_description: There is no home for the wandering Throe. Apparent in some fierce battles, but hidden from others, his myth is both his curse and inconsistency brought to the battlefield. Once believed to be led by demons unknown, only fear now leads this wandering stag through the plains of war.

items.name: Mana Pool
items.item_description: From a darkness unknown spills infinite power.

items.name: Baekho
items.item_description: From the west, the White Tiger came, as the leaves grew golden in the Fall and the first touch of frost cut like steel through the mountain air. Strength and bravery are Baekho's gifts, delivered with a growl alongside your items.

items.name: Announcer: Trine
items.item_description: This pack replaces the Default announcer with the soothing tones of Trine's tale-weaving narrator.

items.name: Celestial Observatory
items.item_description: This ancient ward has stood watch nearly as long as the stars themselves.

items.name: Scuttling Scotty
items.item_description: Separated from his flock in an ice storm, the adventurous young pengling Scotty wandered the Blueheart Glacier, starving and alone, until he found himself rescued by a certain young Ice Maiden. Crystal Maiden nursed him back to health with love and fishy treats. Swearing to return her kindness, Scotty swore off adventuring, and now he has no urge other than to carry supplies and treats to those in need.

items.name: Mega-Kills: Trine
items.item_description: This pack replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the soothing tones of Trine's tale-weaving narrator.

items.name: Recipe: Unusual Artificer's Hammer
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of items and produce an Unusual Artificer's Hammer.

items.name: Recipe: Artificer's Hammer
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of items and produce an Artificer's Hammer. The hammer can be used to extract gems from items, but at the cost of destroying the gemmed item.

items.name: Recipe: Artificer's Chisel
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of items and produce an chisel that can be used to add sockets to items.

items.name: Recipe: Artificer's Brand
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of items and produce an Artificer's Brand. The brand can be used to make a courier unusual bu adding effect and color sockets to it.

items.name: MLG Stronghold
items.item_description: Even the mightiest offensive may fail against firm fortification.

items.name: MLG Scalehound
items.item_description: Found on the wild meadows of Druud, these vicious beasts are easily trained as beasts of burden and camp watchdogs.

items.name: Recipe: Materialize Item
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of magical essences and produce a random item.

items.name: Recipe: Materialize Item
items.item_description: This recipe will combine a number of magical essences and produce a random item.

items.name: Hollow Jack
items.item_description:
Tired of hauling a Diretide sack?
	Just hand it off to Hollow Jack!

items.name: Treasure of Earth Essence
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key of Earth Essence</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Treasure of Ember Essence
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key of Ember Essence</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Watchful Sotdae
items.item_description: Let no vile spirit or foe pass unseen.

items.name: Recipe: Hollow Jack
items.item_description: This recipe will combine an item from the Ghastly Treasure of Diretide with any Cursed item to produce a Hollow Jack courier.

items.name: MLG Tethered Sentinel
items.item_description: Ever present, ever watchful.

items.name: Locked Gemstone Cache
items.item_description: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Each chest series comes with a different selection of possible loot.

items.name: Platinum Baby Roshan
items.item_description: A unique and glistening trophy awarded to the deadliest heroes to face Sugar Rush Roshan.

items.name: Coco the Courageous
items.item_description: True courage is not how high you can hold a sword but how high you can hold your spirit... And sometimes, even the strongest of heroes need their spirit boosted! Introducing Coco, a courageous courier of the Redpaw Brewery, determined to bring brew to the battlefield at any cost! No longer shall a heroes thirst go unquenched! The call for brew is sacred and by oath it must be upheld! The brew must flow.

items.name: Eye of Lyralei
items.item_description: Created by the elements of nature to assist a hero in battle.

items.name: Name Tag
items.item_description:
Double or right-click this tool and use it on an item in your backpack to give the item a <font color='#9da1a9'>customized name</font>.
	Name Tags are consumable items, and may only be used once. A named item can be reverted to its original state by right-clicking the item in the backpack and pressing the 'Restore' option.

items.name: Desc Tag
items.item_description:
Double or right-click this tool and use it on an item in your backpack to give the item a <font color='#9da1a9'>customized description</font>.
	Description Tags are consumable items, and may only be used once. A described item can be reverted to its original state by right-clicking the item in the backpack and pressing the 'Restore' option.

items.name: Armory Expander
items.item_description: Use this tool to add 120 slots to your armory. Armory Expanders are consumable items that may only be used once.

items.name: Treasure Key
items.item_description: Used to open locked <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Chests</font>. Double click or right-click the key in your backpack and select the chest you want to open.

items.name: 75 Battle Bonus (3 Days)
items.item_description: Use this item to increase the rate at which you earn <font color='#9da1a9'>Battle Points</font> by <font color='#9da1a9'>75%</font> for 3 days. Additionally, you will grant other players a stacking <font color='#9da1a9'>15%</font> bonus to their <font color='#9da1a9'>Battle Points</font> rate.

items.name: 75 Battle Bonus (6 Days)
items.item_description: Use this item to increase the rate at which you earn <font color='#9da1a9'>Battle Points</font> by <font color='#9da1a9'>75%</font> for 6 days. Additionally, you will grant other players a stacking <font color='#9da1a9'>15%</font> bonus to their <font color='#9da1a9'>Battle Points</font> rate.

items.name: Pile of Coal
items.item_description: Delicious, delicious coal!

items.name: Gift - 1 Player
items.item_description: When used, this Action Item gives a <font color='#9da1a9'>random item drop</font> to a <font color='#9da1a9'>random person</font> on the server (not you). You can use this item by equipping it as an action item and then activating it during a match.

items.name: Gift - 9 Players

items.name: OLD - The Defense 3
items.item_description: The Defense is back with new sponsors ROCCAT and own3D.tv. Watch 24 invited professional teams and 8 teams from an open qualifier battle for a prize pool of $20,000. This ticket will entitle you to over 100 broadcasted matches by Toby "Tobi Wan Kenobi" Dawson as well as one exclusive courier.

items.name: The Deadly Nightshade Set
items.item_description: On the trail of a curious cipher which might decrypt an ancient codex of the Hidden Temple, Lanaya stumbled upon a cache of hidden garments in an arboretum sacred to the Three Shades. Three garments, wrapped in the petals of an enormous nightshade, on which were inscribed the names of those ethereal Shades that lent their attributes to each piece: madness, terror and death. Most would consider these poor qualities in their attire. But for Templar Assassin, donning the Deadly Nightshade is an accelerant to wisdom. Includes all of the items in 'The Deadly Nightshade' set for Templar Assassin:

items.name: The Riftshadow Roamer's Set
items.item_description: Trinkets and tall tales are just a few of the ways a drifter can make a living out in Riftshadow, but there's a lot more in the waste if you know how to look, and where. You'll want a guide and someone who knows their way in a fight, that should let you scratch the surface and take in some history. Getting rich from the ruins though, that's another matter. If you want to learn Riftshadow's darkest secrets, you better tip well and know how to keep your mouth shut. This here bundle includes all of the items in 'The Riftshadow Roamer' set for Meepo:

items.name: The Stormcrow's Spirit Set
items.item_description:
In hushed tones, legends have long been whispered of the near-mythical stormcrows.
	
	Enormous, powerful and reclusive, these strange, scarce birds range across the highest peaks of the Prefect mountains, hidden from the world by a constant bank of dark cloud. Their rare sighting are considered ill omens, said to portend of storms soon to follow.
	
	Legends also tell of those few who have dared face the dangerous trials required to harness the power of these creatures for themselves. 
	
	For the only way to return after stealing the egg of a stormcrow - a potent source of power - is to wrestle control of one of the enormous black birds and ride it down to the ground, miles below.  Includes all of the items in 'The Stormcrow's Spirit' set for Witch Doctor:

items.name: Winter Snowdrop Set
items.item_description: It is little known of Crystal Maiden, that in her long study of the Frozen Arts, she once greatly displeased her Ice Wizard master and to restore herself to his graces and prove worthy of his instruction, she passed a year dwelling in the climes of slush where the Blueheart Glacier spends itself at the edge of the Boiling Sea. Here, where snow had never fallen, Rylai spent months in deep meditation, mastering her powers, before waking one afternoon with a single frigid word upon her lips: 'Snowdrop!' For a moment, the steam that filled the air turned to ice, and the warm precipitation became a softly falling snow. When she returned to her old teacher, she found him waiting with a smile, fully aware of the magic she had wrought, as he presented her this outfit to show her worth and mastery. Contains all of the items in the 'Snowdrop' set for Crystal Maiden:

items.name: Bastion Announcer Pack
items.item_description: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the euphemistic keen-eyed wisdom of Bastion's narrator, also known as Rucks.

items.item_description: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the double-edged wit of Axe.

items.name: The Pirate Cap'n Announcer Pack
items.item_description: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with Captain Matey's scurrrrvy play-by-play.

items.name: The Slithereen Exile Set
items.item_description: No Slithereen may fail. Though Slithice swam victorious at the battle of Crey, a single jeweled chalice was taken. The punishment for the lost bauble: banishment. So she wandered the deeps, bitterly searching for the chalice, and where once dwelt honor and humility now crept the tendrils of cruelty and malice. If she was to be exiled, then so be it. She shed the lighter tones of her ancestral armor, instead taking up darker armaments, and all who looked upon her felt the indomitable will of the exiled siren. This bundle contains all of the items in 'The Slithereen Exile' set for Naga Siren:

items.name: Hunter of the Red Talon Set
items.item_name: Hunter of the Red Talon Set
items.item_description: Since escaping bondage in kingdom of Slom, Beastmaster has always drawn strength from the natural world around him. When other heroes turn to steel or magic, Beastmaster turns to more ancient implements: feathers, leathers, bones and fur.  With these primitive tools, he's proven his worth against even the most well-armed knight. This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Hunter of the Red Talon' set for Beastmaster:

items.name: Ancestral Trappings Set
items.item_description: The early shadow priests of the Dezun Order were said to have woven their vestments in utter darkness, for only in the total absence of light could they properly channel the essence of the Nothl Realm into the fabrics. It was believed that once complete, the enchantment would grow stronger as the garment aged. The oldest regalia are therefore not only prized for their hallowed creators, but for the heightened Nothl power they bestow upon the wearer. Contains all of the items in the 'Ancestral Trappings' set for Dazzle:

items.name: The Burden of Eleven Curses Set
items.item_name: The Burden of Eleven Curses Set
items.item_description: He that burns and is not consumed now walks the battlefied, shielded by the ancient promise of the Eleven Curses. Eleven Eyes, eleven seals, eleven curses. All to insure victory in even the worst of battles. Contains all of the items in 'The Burden of Eleven Curses' set for Doom Bringer:

items.name: The Mysterious Vagabond Set
items.item_description: In the final years of the Sordid Era, after thirteen seasons of drought, shamanic ways fell into disrepute, with all itinerant mages blamed for failing crops and disease. In order to continue his travels, Rhasta was forced to adopt a new appearance. While still offering many of the same services, during the end of this Era he disclaimed all knowledge of shamanism and professed only the knowledge that any vagabond might acquire along the road, and practice (in a strictly nonprofessional sense) for a few coins. Thus he survived into the next era, when many another was separated from their hide and stretched out along the roads as a warning to the next shaman who might happen along. Contains all of the items in the 'Mysterious Vagabond' set for Shadow Shaman:

items.name: Gear of the Tally-Ho Hunter Set
items.item_name: Gear of the Tally-Ho Hunter Set
items.item_description: Long ago exiled from the valleys of Knollen, Sniper has travelled to many lands, fought in many battles, and learned much along the way. From these adventures, he has garnered mementos of his travels, collecting armor and weapons as he strives to fulfill the prophecy of his youth, in the hope of one day rejoining the keen folk of his ancestral village. Contains all of the items in the 'Gear of the Tally-Ho Hunter' set for Sniper:

items.name: Rider of the Storm Set
items.item_description: The scarred and battle-hardened veteran of many conflicts, Disruptor knows that even the best Stormcrafter is never fully in control of a storm, but merely a vector for its power. Astride the last of the legendary Archtyrex stryders, Disruptor rides into battle wielding the ancient power of the upland storms.  Stormriders laugh in the face of order and through force of will bend storms to their bidding.  Clad in the armor of his ancestors, and riding his scaly steed, Disruptor is a true Rider of the Storm.

items.name: The Brood Queen Set
items.item_description: Many are the knights and noble youths who have intruded on the hunting grounds of the Broodmother, disturbing her peace with the clatter of armor, their boots setting atwitch her silken web. The intruders are like succulent shelled insects upon whose innards she's gorged, all the while growing curious of the adornments that drape their bodies, until that day when a blacksmith found his way into her web.  Armor he promised her, the finest in the land, if only she would set him free. And so a deal was struck, and the blacksmith measured, and toiled, taking as his materials the finest steel to be found among the husked corpses of silk-wrapped knights.  When the new armor was finished, the spider kept her promise and set the blacksmith free.  Then she watched her brood devour him. Contains all of the items in the 'Brood Queen' set for Broodmother:

items.name: The Gallows Understudy Set
items.item_description:
Far from the temples of the Flayed Twins, Bloodseeker stumbled upon a land that lauded execution above sacrifice, relying on hempen rope and metal blades instead of black stone and the will of bloodthirsty gods. Yet there was something in their crude approach that appealed to him, and so he spent a season studying the executioners, watching from the crowd that turned out for every morbid spectacle, until he realized that the mob itself was the god to whom they made their sacrifices. With a leer that matched those to be seen on the faces of the enrapt audience, he made his way home to share the lessons he had learned with his own bloody masters of the priestly caste. 
	
	Includes all items from the Gallows Understudy Set.
